(87, 180, 5, NULL, '<p>Located in north-eastern Bangladesh, Tanguar haor is a river basin and a unique wetland ecosystem of national importance. The tour is ideal for you if you want to experience both adventures and serenity. You’ll have a traditional wooden boat with the necessary amenities as your home during the tour. During the tour, you’ll have mouth-watering delicacies more than three times a day while watching the beauty of the wetland from your private boat. The tour will also let you explore the picturesque beauty of Shimul Bagan, bathe in the mirror-like clear water, visit the popular lakes, and enjoy the view of the hills around. Hence, the tour will give you both tranquility to your soul and stories to tell.</p><p><strong>Places that will be covered in this tour are</strong></p><ul><li>Tekerghat</li><li>Shimul Bagan</li><li>Barikka Tila</li><li>Jadukata River</li><li>Shahid Siraj Lake/ Quarry Lake / Niladri Lake</li><li>Tanguar Haor Watch Tower</li><li>Koroch tree forest</li></ul><p><strong>Food Menu</strong></p><p>1st day-</p><ul><li>Breakfast: Chicken khichuri, egg curry, begun bhaja, salad and water</li><li>Morning Snacks: Dry cake/biscuits/fruits and tea.</li><li>Lunch: Plain rice, chicken Curry/fish Curry, daal, vegetables, fish bhorta, and water.</li><li>Evening snacks: Noodles and tea</li><li>Dinner: Plain rice, duck curry, bhorta, daal, vegetables, salad and water.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>2nd Day-</p><ul><li>Breakfast: Chicken khichuri, egg curry, begun bhaja, salad and water</li><li>Morning Snacks: Dry cake/biscuits/fruits and tea.</li><li>Lunch: Plain rice, chicken Curry/fish Curry, daal, vegetables, fish bhorta, and water.</li><li>Evening snacks: Noodles and tea.<br><br><strong>child policy:</strong><br><strong>0-3 years free</strong><br><strong>3-6 years 2500/- for food</strong><br><strong>7-9 years 60%</strong><br><strong>10 years 100%.</strong></li></ul>', 'facility_images/et2l2jmg5eBMHyrkWSEMHqA1daBmwYMYarRQuzAG.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-03 09:50:45', '2025-05-28 10:15:13', '20'),
(88, 180, 6, NULL, '<p>Information about the Boat: Jolnibas</p><p>hings to keep in mind</p><p>An adequate amount of tea will be served on the boat. Travelers can have tea anytime they want.<br>There is a water filter on the boat. Travelers can drink water from that water filter.<br>The times mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather conditions, tides in the river, convenience of the travelers, and other unavoidable circumstances. Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator/host/organizer in case of such circumstances.<br>The travelers are requested to contact with the tour operator/host/organizer incase they face any kind of trouble/problem during the tour.<br>Always be respectful of the rules and guidelines of the tourist spots.<br>Do not litter, use a disposable bag as a portable trash bin.<br>Travelers are strongly encouraged not to misbehave with any local inhabitants. Travelers are asked to seek help from the tour operator/host/organizer in case they need to contact any local people.<br>There is no separate dining space on this boat. Everyone will have their meals on the open deck of the boat.<br>Consumption of any sort of drugs is strictly prohibited.<br>In the case of a group tour, there will be other people who will travel with you.<br>If anyone wants to travel to Lakmachora on a bike then the traveler will have to bear&nbsp;the&nbsp;bike&nbsp;fare.</p>', 'facility_images/yLcMMIfOaQtJfHKIpnbcEMiTMeFMCcCvX3ofNAr3.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-03 09:51:36', '2025-06-01 05:54:53', '20'),
(89, 180, 7, NULL, '<p>Travelers are suggested to carry the following item,</p><ul><li>Personal clothing</li><li>Towel/Gamcha</li><li>Sunglass</li><li>Hat</li><li>Personal Medicine</li><li>Personal Hygiene Products</li><li>Camera with extra battery</li><li>A copy of NID Card</li><li>Dry Food</li><li>Mosquito repellent lotion/cream</li><li>Sunscreen</li><li>Flashlight/Torch Light</li><li>Power Bank</li></ul>', 'facility_images/dmRwTIMARn1HtYosWnLEhYpZ9sxAdX2aJkKJskGC.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-03 09:52:07', '2025-03-03 09:52:07', '21'),
(90, 180, 10, NULL, '<p>Option 1</p><p><strong>Private Group Tour from Dhaka</strong></p><p>Minimum 10 travelers needed for this tour. The private tour starts from Dhaka. Travelers, coming from anywhere in Bangladesh, will have manage their own transportation from/to Dhaka.</p><p>Option 2</p><p><strong>Public Group Tour</strong></p><p>This is a group tour. There will be other travelers who will also participate in this tour.</p><p>Option 3</p><p><strong>Private Group Tour From Sunamganj</strong></p><p>Minimum 10 travelers needed for this tour. The private tour starts from Sunamganj. Travelers, coming from anywhere in Bangladesh, will have manage their own transportation from/to Sunamganj.</p>', 'facility_images/6fL6pioZavb2hWE90SMyzlLB4LWNiQ64pcXxn2X4.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-03 09:53:06', '2025-03-03 09:53:06', '16'),
(91, 180, 13, NULL, '<p>Cancellation* &nbsp;<br>To cancel any tour, an email has to be sent to *bookmebdltd@gmail.com* mentioning the tour booking ID, phone number and details about the cancellation. &nbsp;<br>Travelers are responsible for notifying Bookme of any cancellations as soon as possible. &nbsp;<br>The email acts as the final application for cancellation. Phone calls to Bookme\'s hotline or contacting any team member directly will not be considered as cancellation requests. &nbsp;<br>The time of sending the email will be considered as the time of cancellation. &nbsp;<br>In cases of exceptional circumstances, such as acts of God, natural disasters, or mandatory government closures, Bookme may offer alternative dates for the tour or a full refund, at Bookme\'s discretion. &nbsp;<br>If a tour is cancelled by the tour operator due to unforeseen circumstances, travelers will be entitled to a full refund of the tour fee. &nbsp;<br>This policy is subject to change without prior notice. Please refer to the website or booking confirmation voucher/invoice for the most up-to-date information. &nbsp;<br>Tours booked for blackout dates, government holidays, and festival periods are non-refundable and non-cancellable. &nbsp;<br>This cancellation policy may not be applicable in case of national emergency/ lockdown/ political unrest/ natural disaster etc. &nbsp;<br>This policy is applicable to all tour cancellations, regardless of the reason for cancellation.</p><p>*Refund* &nbsp;<br>80% of the fees will be refunded if the booking is canceled more than Twenty-One (21) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>50% of the fees will be refunded if the booking is canceled within Fourteen (14) to Twenty-One (21) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>30% of the tour fee will be refunded if the booking is canceled within Seven (7) to Fourteen (14) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>Refund will not be provided if the tour is cancelled less than Seven (7) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>Convenience fees and insurance fees are non-refundable and will be deducted from the paid amount. &nbsp;<br>All refunds will be processed within seven (7) working days.</p><p>*Child Policy* &nbsp;<br>No fee will be needed for children below the age of three (3). No separate seat will be provided in case of transportation and accommodation. &nbsp;<br>75% fee must be paid for any child between the age of four (4) and ten (10) years old. &nbsp;<br>Full amount of money must be paid for anyone above ten (10) years old.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Refund</strong><br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>80% of the fees will be refunded if the booking is canceled more than Twenty-One (21) days before the beginning of the experience/tour.</li><li>50% of the fees will be refunded if the booking is canceled within Fourteen (14) to Twenty-One (21) days before the beginning of the experience/tour.</li><li>30% of the tour fee will be refunded if the booking is canceled within Seven (7) to Fourteen (14) days before the beginning of the experience/tour.</li><li>Refund will not be provided if the tour is cancelled less than Seven (7) days before the beginning of the experience/tour.</li><li>Convenience fees and insurance fees are non-refundable and will be deducted from the paid amount.</li><li>All refunds will be processed within five (5) working days.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Child Policy</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>No fee will be needed for children below the age of four (4). No separate seat will be provided in case of transportation and accommodation.</li><li>50% fee must be paid for any child between the age of five (5) and ten (10) years old.&nbsp;</li><li>Full amount of money must be paid for anyone above ten (10) years old.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'facility_images/6p5qO9IMnW6T4OFMJM2mKYrZ0UbGZwtmKoT6LOV2.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-03 09:55:41', '2025-05-13 05:55:18',