</li><li><strong>Afternoon Snacks:</strong> Noodles/ Murimakha, Tea and Drinking Water.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/94rzN8lysx6AgRcq1cBZ2JCOtHSNUaA7YmrY66PA.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 05:08:35', '2025-03-04 05:08:35', '16'),
(119, 202, 6, 'Additional information', '<p>Information about the Boat: Rongila Baroi</p><p>This boat is one of the finest boats of Tanguar Haor that provides professional tourist service. This wooden boat does not get heated up during scorching sun or daytime.</p><p><strong>Capacity:</strong> The 8-cabin boat has an occupancy of 16 to 18 people. Additionally, 2 single cabins can accommodate 2 more people. With 2 large windows each, the 8 deluxe haor-view cabins have the following capacity:</p><p>Standard capacity = 2 people x 8 = 16 people</p><p>Maximum capacity = 3 people x 8 = 24 people</p><p>Each of the 8 deluxe haor-view rooms includes an attached bathroom, Including two single beds, <strong>the total capacity is 18-26+ people.</strong></p><p><strong>Sophisticated Design:</strong> Each space is designed by an architect, with minimalist interior design. Proper lighting and skylights prevent the corridors from feeling confined, ensuring proper ventilation.</p><p><strong>Engine</strong>: Instead of a shallow engine, we have a powerful 6-cylinder Japanese engine, which results in minimal cabin noise. Additionally, there is the benefit of a silent generator for extended periods.</p><p><strong>Comfort:</strong> Topper beds, hotel pillows, comforters, toiletries - on-call room service is available.</p><p><strong>Safety: </strong>For personal safety, there are more than 30 life jackets, including special-sized life jackets for children, and 10 buoys. We also have fire extinguishers (3 types), nighttime security with their own guards, and CCTV cameras.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Things to keep in mind</p><ul><li>Adequate amount of tea will be served on the boat. Travelers can have tea anytime they want.</li><li>There is a water filter on the boat. Travelers can drink water from that water filter.</li><li>The time mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather condition, tides in the river, convenience of the travelers and other unavoidable circumstances. Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator/host/organizer in case of such circumstance.</li><li>The travelers are requested to contact with the tour operator/host/organizer incase they face any kind of trouble/problem during the tour.</li><li>Always be respectful of the rules and guidelines of the tourist spots.</li><li>Do not litter, use a disposable bag as a portable trash bin.</li><li>Travelers are strongly encouraged not to misbehave with any local inhabitant. Travelers are asked to seek help from tour operator/host/organizer incase they need to contact with any local people.</li><li>There is no separate dinning space on this boat. Everyone will have their meals on the open deck of the boat.</li><li>Consumption of any sort of drugs is strictly prohibited.</li><li>In case of group tour, there will be other people who will travel with you.</li><li>If anyone wants to travel to lakmachora in a bike then the traveler will have to bear the bike fare.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/oBtc9i1pCVWMOSXNqj35ACfuWHzf7YgQ07PvJTjj.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 05:09:37', '2025-03-04 05:09:37', '14'),
