(130, 199, 5, 'Description', '<p><strong>Day 1</strong></p><ul><li>Breakfast: Fried rice, chicken curry, egg curry, pickle, tea, water.</li><li>Snacks: Seasonal fruits, cake, tea, water.</li><li>Lunch: Plain rice, mashed vegetables (2 items), vegetables, small fish, large fish, local chicken, lentil, salad, tea, water.</li><li>Evening Snack: Noodles/puri, singara, muri-makha, tea, water.</li><li>Dinner: Plain rice, duck curry, fish/chicken, vegetables, lentil, salad, water.</li></ul><p><strong>Day 2</strong></p><ul><li>Breakfast Fried rice, chicken curry, egg curry, pickle, tea, water.</li><li>Snacks: Biscuit/noodles/muri-makha, tea, water.</li><li>Lunch: Plain rice, mashed vegetables (2 items), vegetables, fish/chicken, lentil, salad, tea, water.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/vRZwthEzii0C5nrQyV7Gf0KCSxUJuclmtxghKwkB.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 05:54:52', '2025-03-04 05:54:52', '22'),
(131, 199, 6, 'Additional information', '<p>Information about the Boat: Haorer Sultan 2</p><p>This boat is one of the finest boats of Tanguar Haor that provides professional tourist service. This wooden boat does not get heated up during scorching sun or daytime.</p><ul><li>25 people can be accommodated inside the boat</li><li>This boat has a 130-watt solar panel</li><li>4 Air Conditioned Cabins with attached toilets</li><li>4 cabins with attached toilets</li><li>2 cabins with common toilets</li><li>This boat has a water filter to store 300 liters of fresh water for regular use.</li><li>Twenty life vests / Life jackets</li><li>Private cook</li><li>Power sockets (charging facility)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Things to keep in mind</strong></p><ul><li>An adequate amount of tea will be served on the boat. Travelers can have tea anytime they want.</li><li>There is a water filter on the boat. Travelers can drink water from that water filter.</li><li>The times mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather conditions, tides in the river, convenience of the travelers, and other unavoidable circumstances. Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator/host/organizer in case of such circumstances.</li><li>The travelers are requested to contact with the tour operator/host/organizer incase they face any kind of trouble/problem during the tour.</li><li>Always be respectful of the rules and guidelines of the tourist spots.</li><li>Do not litter, use a disposable bag as a portable trash bin.</li><li>Travelers are strongly encouraged not to misbehave with any local inhabitants. Travelers are asked to seek help from the tour operator/host/organizer in case they need to contact any local people.</li><li>There is no separate dining space on this boat. Everyone will have their meals on the open deck of the boat.</li><li>Consumption of any sort of drugs is strictly prohibited.</li><li>In the case of a group tour, there will be other people who will travel with you.</li><li>If anyone wants to travel to Lakmachora on a bike then the traveler will have to bear the bike fare.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/0En0jsTCcW5Sf6AfMAOSgG4CdQShhudXk0TkMuBM.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 05:55:44', '2025-03-04 05:55:44', '9'),
