(161, 200, 4, 'inclusion', '<ul><li>✔All the facilities of the boat<br>✔Private Cook<br>✔Breakfast - Days 1 and 2<br>✔Lunch - Days 1 and 2<br>✔Dinner - Days 1 and 2<br>✔Snacks Day 1 and 2<br>✔Life Vests<br>✔Night Guard</li><li>✕Dhaka - Sunamganj - Dhaka Non Ac Bus Transportation (For Group Tour only)<br>✕Any personal expenses<br>✕Anything that is not mentioned in the inclusions.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/zTxpRawRZdBIh47NOtm0Sii4GNsADKSpNCQGEkQI.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 08:23:22', '2025-03-04 08:23:22', '15'),
(162, 200, 5, 'Description', '<p>Nestled in north-eastern Bangladesh, Tanguar Haor is a remarkable river basin and wetland ecosystem of national significance. This tour is perfect for those seeking a blend of adventure and peace. You\'ll stay on a traditional wooden boat, equipped with all necessary amenities, serving as your home throughout the journey. Savor delectable meals more than three times a day as you take in the stunning views of the wetland from your floating abode. The tour includes exploring the scenic Shimul Bagan, swimming in crystal-clear waters, visiting popular lakes, and enjoying the surrounding hills. To elevate your experience, live local musical sessions are arranged, providing soulful tranquility and memorable tales to share.</p><p>Places that will be covered in this tour are</p><ul><li>Tanguar Haor</li><li>Watch Tower</li><li>Jadukata River</li><li>Barikka Tila</li><li>Teker Ghat</li><li>Shahid Siraj Lake / Quarry Lake / Niladri Lake</li><li>Khorchar Haor</li><li>Shonir Haor</li></ul><p><strong>Food Menu:&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Day - 1&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Welcome Drinks&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Breakfast:</strong>&nbsp;Khichuri, Fried Egg, Fried Chicken, Fried Eggplant, Pickles, Salad,Drinking Water, Tea</li><li><strong>Snacks:</strong> Spicy Puffed Rice, Fruits, Tea, Drinking Water.</li><li><strong>Lunch</strong>: Rice, Boal Fish, Fish Bhorta, Small Fish Fry, Mashed Potato, Murighanta, Salad, Drinking Water, Tea, Sweets.</li><li><strong>Aftenoon Snacks:</strong> Eggplant, Chop, Tea.</li><li><strong>Dinner:</strong> Rice, Mashed Brinjal, Small Fish/Medium Fish Fry, Roasted Duck, Daal, Salad, Drinking Water, Tea</li></ul><p><strong>Day - 2</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Breakfast: </strong>Chicken Akhni, Small Fish Fry, Pickles, Salad, Drinking Water, Tea,</li><li><strong>Snacks:</strong> Cookies/ Singara/ Noodles, Tea</li><li><strong>Lunch:</strong> Rice, Kalbaus/ Aair Fish, Roasted Chicken,Mashed Tomato, Daal, Salad,Drinking Water, Tea.</li><li><strong>Snacks:</strong> Eggplant Chop, Coffee.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/n62UHUEWkJhWnrd0i5eufxZ70RZauZWEa5TPg6P0.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 08:23:45', '2025-03-04 08:23:45', '16'),
(163, 200, 6, 'Additional information', '<p>Information about the Boat: Hijol</p><p>This boat is one of the finest boats of Tanguar Haor that provides professional tourist service. This wooden boat does not get heated up during scorching sun or daytime</p><p>15 People can be accommodated inside the boat, 5 couple rooms, Besides, 4 people can sleep comfortably in the lobby,</p><p>Hijoli has 5 attached/attached washrooms in all 5 rooms.</p><p>This boat has a 130-watt solar panel.</p><p>Five electric fans and six lights.</p><p>This boat has a water filter to store 300 liters of fresh water for regular use.</p><p>Fifteen life vests / Life jackets</p><p>Private cook</p><p>Power sockets (charging facility)</p><p>Amenities for prayer</p><p>Rooftop with 1,500 square feet of space</p><p>Rooftop dining</p><p>Fire safety equipment</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Things to keep in mind</p><ul><li>Adequate amount of tea will be served on the boat. Travelers can have tea anytime they want.</li><li>There is a water filter on the boat. Travelers can drink water from that water filter.</li><li>The time mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather condition, tides in the river, convenience of the travelers and other unavoidable circumstances. Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator/host/organizer in case of such circumstance.</li><li>The travelers are requested to contact with the tour operator/host/organizer incase they face any kind of trouble/problem during the tour.</li><li>Always be respectful of the rules and guidelines of the tourist spots.</li><li>Do not litter, use a disposable bag as a portable trash bin.</li><li>Travelers are strongly encouraged not to misbehave with any local inhabitant. Travelers are asked to seek help from tour operator/host/organizer incase they need to contact with any local people.</li><li>There is no separate dinning space on this boat. Everyone will have their meals on the open deck of the boat.</li><li>Consumption of any sort of drugs is strictly prohibited.</li><li>In case of group tour, there will be other people who will travel with you.</li><li>If anyone wants to travel to lakmachora in a bike then the traveler will have to bear the bike fare.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/npO6MOrzZaaCe0OwbhrIRqNGqwaxccDCkhMUeKQ4.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 08:24:13', '2025-03-04 08:24:13', '16'),
(164, 200, 7, 'Travel tips', '<p>Travelers are suggested to carry the following item,</p><ul><li>Personal clothing</li><li>Towel/Gamcha</li><li>Sunglass</li><li>Hat</li><li>Personal Medicine</li><li>Personal Hygiene Products</li><li>Camera with extra battery</li><li>A copy of NID Card</li></ul>', 'facility_images/qI0kKlsYHVyhDuuCcdwJAuXfxdj7BAwPK5ncaeU6.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 08:24:40', '2025-03-04 08:24:40', '21'),
(165, 200, 13, 'Policy', '<p>Cancellation* &nbsp;<br>To cancel any tour, an email has to be sent to *bookmebdltd@gmail.com* mentioning the tour booking ID, phone number and details about the cancellation. &nbsp;<br>Travelers are responsible for notifying Bookme of any cancellations as soon as possible. &nbsp;<br>The email acts as the final application for cancellation. Phone calls to Bookme\'s hotline or contacting any team member directly will not be considered as cancellation requests. &nbsp;<br>The time of sending the email will be considered as the time of cancellation. &nbsp;<br>In cases of exceptional circumstances, such as acts of God, natural disasters, or mandatory government closures, Bookme may offer alternative dates for the tour or a full refund, at Bookme\'s discretion. &nbsp;<br>If a tour is cancelled by the tour operator due to unforeseen circumstances, travelers will be entitled to a full refund of the tour fee. &nbsp;<br>This policy is subject to change without prior notice. Please refer to the website or booking confirmation voucher/invoice for the most up-to-date information. &nbsp;<br>Tours booked for blackout dates, government holidays, and festival periods are non-refundable and non-cancellable. &nbsp;<br>This cancellation policy may not be applicable in case of national emergency/ lockdown/ political unrest/ natural disaster etc. &nbsp;<br>This policy is applicable to all tour cancellations, regardless of the reason for cancellation.</p><p>*Refund* &nbsp;<br>80% of the fees will be refunded if the booking is canceled more than Twenty-One (21) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>50% of the fees will be refunded if the booking is canceled within Fourteen (14) to Twenty-One (21) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>30% of the tour fee will be refunded if the booking is canceled within Seven (7) to Fourteen (14) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>Refund will not be provided if the tour is cancelled less than Seven (7) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>Convenience fees and insurance fees are non-refundable and will be deducted from the paid amount. &nbsp;<br>All refunds will be processed within seven (7) working days.</p><p>*Child Policy* &nbsp;<br>No fee will be needed for children below the age of three (3). No separate seat will be provided in case of transportation and accommodation. &nbsp;<br>75% fee must be paid for any child between the age of four (4) and ten (10) years old. &nbsp;<br>Full amount of money must be paid for anyone above ten (10) years old.</p>', 'facility_images/pDgK5J5S3Wwfa5MLS34b3kOKKYSwF00evoMC9DSz.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-04 08:25:23', '2025-03-04 08:25:23', '14'),
