(270, 240, 4, 'inclusion', '<ul><li>✔Sightseeing as per itinerary<br>✔Accommodation in Boat<br>✔Breakfast (Day 1 and 2)<br>✔Morning snacks (Day 1 and 2)<br>✔Lunch (Day 1 and 2)<br>✔Dinner (Day 1 and 2)<br>✔Evening Snacks (Day 1 and 2)<br>✔Life vest/jacket<br>✔Experienced cook<br>✔Experienced boat driver<br>✔Tour guide</li><li>✕Any type of personal expenses<br>✕Anything which is not mentioned in the inclusions.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/B5CmEt2LwF1Hrk7XZhWOwcnEU4J64cF4zIyb5eea.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-06 06:02:49', '2025-03-06 06:02:49', '16'),
(271, 240, 5, 'Description', '<p>Located in north-eastern Bangladesh, Tanguar haor is a river basin and a unique wetland ecosystem of national importance. The tour is ideal for you if you want to experience both adventures and serenity. You’ll have a traditional wooden boat with the necessary amenities as your home during the tour. During the tour, you’ll have mouth-watering delicacies more than three times a day while watching the beauty of the wetland from your private boat. The tour will also let you explore the picturesque beauty of Shimul Bagan, bathe in the mirror-like clear water, visit the popular lakes, and enjoy the view of the hills around. Hence, the tour will give you both tranquility to your soul and stories to tell.</p><p><strong>Places that will be covered in this tour are</strong></p><ul><li>Tekerghat</li><li>Shimul Bagan</li><li>Barikka Tila</li><li>Jadukata River</li><li>Shahid Siraj Lake/ Quarry Lake / Niladri Lake</li><li>Lakmachora</li><li>Tanguar Haor Watch Tower</li><li>Koroch tree forest</li></ul><p><strong>Food Menu</strong></p><p>1st day-</p><ul><li>Breakfast: Bhuna khichuri, egg curry, bhorta, achar, salad and tea.</li><li>Morning Snacks: Cake/bread/biscuits, fruits and tea.</li><li>Lunch: Plain rice, fish fry/curry, vegetables, bhorta, daal, salad and desert.</li><li>Evening snacks: Semai, tea and coffee.</li><li>Dinner: Plain rice, duck curry, vegetables, bhorta, daal, salad and desert.</li></ul><p>2nd Day-</p><ul><li>Breakfast: Chicken akhni, egg curry, bhorta, achar, salad and tea.</li><li>Morning Snacks: Jhal muri and fruits.</li><li>Lunch: Plain rice, chicken curry, shutki curry, vegetables, daal, salad and desert.</li><li>Evening snacks: Noodles/Pakora and tea</li><li>Dinner: Ruti, duck curry, daal/vegetables, salad and desert.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/GVNLmevCkSqS8R5J0nxDNTGar1kqXJI8EudbDFa6.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-06 06:04:20', '2025-03-06 06:04:20', '14'),
(272, 240, 6, 'Additional information', '<p>Information about the Boat: ডোংগা/ Donga</p><p>This boat is one of the finest boats of Tanguar Haor that provides professional tourist service. This wooden boat does not get heated up during scorching sun or daytime.</p><ul><li>22 people can be accommodated inside the boat</li><li>2 separate toilets with high commode and 1 toilet with low commode</li><li>2 lock door couple cabins</li><li>2 lock door family bunker cabin</li><li>2 open cabins</li><li>Locker facility</li><li>This boat has a water filter which can store 300 liters of fresh water for regular use.</li><li>Twenty life vests / Life jackets</li><li>Private cook</li><li>Power sockets (charging facility)</li><li>Amenities for prayer</li><li>Rooftop dining</li><li>Fire safety equipment</li><li>Recreational games (Chess, Uno, Card, Ludo, Football)</li><li>Experienced tour guide, boat driver and cook.</li></ul><p>Things to keep in mind</p><ul><li>Adequate amount of tea will be served on the boat. Travelers can have tea anytime they want.</li><li>There is a water filter on the boat. Travelers can drink water from that water filter.</li><li>The time mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather condition, tides in the river, convenience of the travelers and other unavoidable circumstances. Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator/host/organizer in case of such circumstance.</li><li>The travelers are requested to contact with the tour operator/host/organizer incase they face any kind of trouble/problem during the tour.</li><li>Always be respectful of the rules and guidelines of the tourist spots.</li><li>Do not litter, use a disposable bag as a portable trash bin.</li><li>Travelers are strongly encouraged not to misbehave with any local inhabitant. Travelers are asked to seek help from tour operator/host/organizer incase they need to contact with any local people.</li><li>There is no separate dinning space on this boat. Everyone will have their meals on the open deck of the boat.</li><li>Consumption of any sort of drugs is strictly prohibited.</li><li>In case of group tour, there will be other people who will travel with you.</li><li>If anyone wants to travel to lakmachora in a bike then the traveler will have to bear the bike fare.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/h8ujMOhgA8R0YV6X0BwVGvGNCdpmN9VmOpq7LEwq.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-06 06:04:51', '2025-03-06 06:04:51', '15'),
(273, 240, 7, 'Travel tips', '<p>Traveling in Tanguar Haor and staying in houseboats can be a unique and rewarding experience. Here are some tips to ensure you have a memorable and enjoyable time:</p><p><strong>During Your Stay:</strong></p><ol><li>Houseboat Comfort: While houseboats offer a unique experience, remember that their facilities might be basic. Expect simple amenities and embrace the rustic charm.</li><li>Respect Nature: Tanguar Haor is a delicate ecosystem. Be respectful of the environment; do not throw waste into the water or disturb wildlife.</li><li>Boat Safety: Houseboats should have safety equipment, including life jackets. Familiarize yourself with their location and wear them when necessary, especially during boat rides.</li><li>Cultural Respect: If interacting with local communities, be polite, ask for permission before taking photographs, and respect their way of life.</li><li>Meal Arrangements: Houseboats often provide meals as part of the package. Enjoy the local cuisine, but communicate any dietary preferences or restrictions in advance.</li><li>Electricity and Connectivity: Be prepared for limited or intermittent electricity and mobile network coverage. Carry portable chargers for your devices.</li></ol><p><strong>Exploring Tanguar Haor:</strong></p><ol><li>Birdwatching<strong>:</strong> Tanguar Haor is a haven for birdwatchers. Bring binoculars and a bird guidebook to identify the diverse avian species.</li><li>Boating<strong>:</strong> Enjoy the serene boat rides on the haor\'s tranquil waters. Sunrise and sunset boat trips offer captivating views. Silent boat rides are available near Tanguar Haor watch tower.</li><li>Fishing: If fishing is allowed, experience traditional fishing techniques with local fishermen.</li><li>Photography: Capture the breathtaking landscapes, vibrant sunsets, and unique moments during your stay.</li></ol><p><strong>Travelers are suggested to carry the following items:</strong></p><ul><li>Personal clothing</li><li>Towel/Gamcha</li><li>Sunglass</li><li>Hat</li><li>Personal Medicine</li><li>Personal Hygiene Products</li><li>Camera with extra battery</li><li>A copy of NID Card</li><li>Dry Food</li><li>Mosquito repellent lotion/cream</li><li>Sunscreen</li><li>Flashlight/Torch Light</li><li>Power Bank and charger</li><li>Swimwear</li><li>Rain gear (raincoat or poncho,&nbsp;umbrella)</li><li>Comfortable footwear (closed-toe shoes, sandals)</li><li>Personal medications</li><li>Trash bags (for responsible disposal)</li><li>Hand sanitizer</li><li>Moisturizer/lip balm</li><li>Small backpack or daypack</li><li>Copy of NID/Passport/Personal identification card.</li></ul>', 'facility_images/8Yc6T8qnRY0TG3hEwXpStUudOutrcUzTf7FhPmaj.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-06 06:05:33', '2025-03-06 06:05:33', '15'),
(274, 240, 13, 'Policy', '<p>Traveling in Tanguar Haor and staying in houseboats can be a unique and rewarding experience. Here are some tips to ensure you have a memorable and enjoyable time:</p><p><strong>During Your Stay:</strong></p><ol><li>Houseboat Comfort: While houseboats offer a unique experience, remember that their facilities might be basic. Expect simple amenities and embrace the rustic charm.</li><li>Respect Nature: Tanguar Haor is a delicate ecosystem. Be respectful of the environment; do not throw waste into the water or disturb wildlife.</li><li>Boat Safety: Houseboats should have safety equipment, including life jackets. Familiarize yourself with their location and wear them when necessary, especially during boat rides.</li><li>Cultural Respect: If interacting with local communities, be polite, ask for permission before taking photographs, and respect their way of life.</li><li>Meal Arrangements: Houseboats often provide meals as part of the package. Enjoy the local cuisine, but communicate any dietary preferences or restrictions in advance.</li><li>Electricity and Connectivity: Be prepared for limited or intermittent electricity and mobile network coverage. Carry portable chargers for your devices.</li></ol><p><strong>Exploring Tanguar Haor:</strong></p><ol><li>Birdwatching<strong>:</strong> Tanguar Haor is a haven for birdwatchers. Bring binoculars and a bird guidebook to identify the diverse avian species.</li><li>Boating<strong>:</strong> Enjoy the serene boat rides on the haor\'s tranquil waters. Sunrise and sunset boat trips offer captivating views. Silent boat rides are available near Tanguar Haor watch tower.</li><li>Fishing: If fishing is allowed, experience traditional fishing techniques with local fishermen.</li><li>Photography: Capture the breathtaking landscapes, vibrant sunsets, and unique moments during your stay.</li></ol><p><strong>Travelers are suggested to carry the following items:</strong></p><ul><li>Personal clothing</li><li>To