(322, 246, 7, 'Travel tips', '<p>Traveling in Tanguar Haor and staying in houseboats can be a unique and rewarding experience. Here are some tips to ensure you have a memorable and enjoyable time:</p><p>During Your Stay:</p><p>Houseboat Comfort: While houseboats offer a unique experience, remember that their facilities might be basic. Expect simple amenities and embrace the rustic charm.<br>Respect Nature: Tanguar Haor is a delicate ecosystem. Be respectful of the environment; do not throw waste into the water or disturb wildlife.<br>Boat Safety: Houseboats should have safety equipment, including life jackets. Familiarize yourself with their location and wear them when necessary, especially during boat rides.<br>Cultural Respect: If interacting with local communities, be polite, ask for permission before taking photographs, and respect their way of life.<br>Meal Arrangements: Houseboats often provide meals as part of the package. Enjoy the local cuisine, but communicate any dietary preferences or restrictions in advance.<br>Electricity and Connectivity: Be prepared for limited or intermittent electricity and mobile network coverage. Carry portable chargers for your devices.<br>Exploring Tanguar Haor:</p><p>Birdwatching: Tanguar Haor is a haven for birdwatchers. Bring binoculars and a bird guidebook to identify the diverse avian species.<br>Boating: Enjoy the serene boat rides on the haor\'s tranquil waters. Sunrise and sunset boat trips offer captivating views. Silent boat rides are available near Tanguar Haor watch tower.<br>Fishing: If fishing is allowed, experience traditional fishing techniques with local fishermen.<br>Photography: Capture the breathtaking landscapes, vibrant sunsets, and unique moments during your stay.<br>Travelers are suggested to carry the following items:</p><p>Personal clothing<br>Towel/Gamcha<br>Sunglass<br>Hat<br>Personal Medicine<br>Personal Hygiene Products<br>Camera with extra battery<br>A copy of NID Card<br>Dry Food<br>Mosquito repellent lotion/cream<br>Sunscreen<br>Flashlight/Torch Light<br>Power Bank and charger<br>Swimwear<br>Rain gear (raincoat or poncho, umbrella)<br>Comfortable footwear (closed-toe shoes, sandals)<br>Personal medications<br>Trash bags (for responsible disposal)<br>Hand sanitizer<br>Moisturizer/lip balm<br>Small backpack or daypack<br>Copy of NID/Passport/Personal identification card.</p>', 'facility_images/G0uvfOTZy1L8CF3GNO4RxjcE0gfHu9zMsGyHRl70.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-06 08:06:16', '2025-03-06 08:06:16', '16'),
(323, 246, 13, 'Policy', '<p>Cancellation* &nbsp;<br>To cancel any tour, an email has to be sent to *bookmebdltd@gmail.com* mentioning the tour booking ID, phone number and details about the cancellation. &nbsp;<br>Travelers are responsible for notifying Bookme of any cancellations as soon as possible. &nbsp;<br>The email acts as the final application for cancellation. Phone calls to Bookme\'s hotline or contacting any team member directly will not be considered as cancellation requests. &nbsp;<br>The time of sending the email will be considered as the time of cancellation. &nbsp;<br>In cases of exceptional circumstances, such as acts of God, natural disasters, or mandatory government closures, Bookme may offer alternative dates for the tour or a full refund, at Bookme\'s discretion. &nbsp;<br>If a tour is cancelled by the tour operator due to unforeseen circumstances, travelers will be entitled to a full refund of the tour fee. &nbsp;<br>This policy is subject to change without prior notice. Please refer to the website or booking confirmation voucher/invoice for the most up-to-date information. &nbsp;<br>Tours booked for blackout dates, government holidays, and festival periods are non-refundable and non-cancellable. &nbsp;<br>This cancellation policy may not be applicable in case of national emergency/ lockdown/ political unrest/ natural disaster etc. &nbsp;<br>This policy is applicable to all tour cancellations, regardless of the reason for cancellation.</p><p>*Refund* &nbsp;<br>80% of the fees will be refunded if the booking is canceled more than Twenty-One (21) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>50% of the fees will be refunded if the booking is canceled within Fourteen (14) to Twenty-One (21) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>30% of the tour fee will be refunded if the booking is canceled within Seven (7) to Fourteen (14) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>Refund will not be provided if the tour is cancelled less than Seven (7) days before the beginning of the experience/tour. &nbsp;<br>Convenience fees and insurance fees are non-refundable and will be deducted from the paid amount. &nbsp;<br>All refunds will be processed within seven (7) working days.</p><p>*Child Policy* &nbsp;<br>No fee will be needed for children below the age of three (3). No separate seat will be provided in case of transportation and accommodation. &nbsp;<br>75% fee must be paid for any child between the age of four (4) and ten (10) years old. &nbsp;<br>Full amount of money must be paid for anyone above ten (10) years old.</p>', 'facility_images/8c8xIYUP5CpIcEwHXY1FIZcArHBTfBSlcytfpJbm.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-06 08:06:35', '2025-03-06 08:06:35', '14'),
(324, 249, 12, 'Summary', '<p>Explore Sundarbans, the largest Mangrove Forest in the world, in its gloriously haunting beauty. The 3 days and 2 nights tour are specially designed to give the visitors an experience of a lifetime. This mangrove forest hosts an amazing faunal &amp; floral diversity, including the probably largest remaining population of Royal Bengal tigers, the endangered estuarine crocodile, Ganges River dolphins as well as an astounding variety of birds. Join the Adventure Cruise and explore this intricate maze of tidal waterways, a natural treasure of Bangladesh. Explore Herbaria, Kochikhali, Dimer Char, Katka,and Karamjal like you never did before. Your journey to the Sundarbans will begin through the world\'s largest mangrove forest. The tour is made safe with armed guards on board from Khulna to Sundarbans. The tour is entertaining, with delectable full-board meals provided on all tour days.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Package Price for MV Utshob:</strong></p><p><strong>Cabin Type-1:</strong> Single Cabin - Common Bath</p><p>Price: BDT 13,000 Per Person</p><p><strong>Cabin Type-2:</strong> Twin Cabin - Common Bath</p><p>Price: BDT 13,000 Per Person</p><p><strong>Cabin Type-3:</strong> Couple Cabin - Attached Bath</p><p>Price: BDT 16,000 Per Person</p><p><strong>Cabin Type-4:</strong> Family Cabin - Attached Bath</p><p>Price: BDT 16,000 Per Person</p><p><strong>Cabin Type-5:</strong> VIP Couple Cabin - Attached Bath</p><p>Price: BDT 18,000 Per Person</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Remember, the cost per person is less if you have more people in your group.</p>', 'facility_images/DBUkpjHrY6P0hgjm9JEGCIazo8KU4cJmQCQSQ9a4.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-22 04:12:15', '2025-03-22 04:12:15', '14'),
(325, 249, 3, 'Location', '<p><strong>Pick-up: </strong>Jailkhana Ghat, Khulna</p>', 'facility_images/N3W7fGNw8BBjp0PJulhMiAJwplQt1x0E2o8tSCaZ.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-22 04:13:45', '2025-03-22 04:13:45', '18'),
(326, 249, 2, 'Timing', '<p>Reporting Time: 7:00 AM Departure Time: 7:30 AM<br><strong>Duration</strong> : 3 days</p>', 'facility_images/R3sKUViUR6Xj825HOix2HzLYzPQDiNI8yB2XCqcc.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-22 04:14:13', '2025-03-22 04:14:13', '16'),
(327, 249, 4, 'inclusion', '<ul><li>✔Two nights’ accommodation on a Single/Double/Twin/Triple/Four Bed-sharing cabin<br>✔All meals during the trip<br>✔All activities inside the forest as per itinerary<br>✔Mineral water for drinking during the trip<br>✔Forest fees &amp; permission (for Bangladeshi nationals only)<br>✔Armed forest guard from the forest department<br>✔An experienced tour Guide<br>✔All-time Tea, Coffee, and drinking water in the lounge room.<br>✔Country boat cruise inside the forest<br>✔All applicable taxes and tolls</li><li>✕Beverages / Drinks - Hard &amp; Soft.<br>✕Items of personal nature - Postage, Phone, Fax, Internet, Medicine, Insurance, Laundry, etc.<br>✕Tips to Guide &amp; Driver.<br>✕Anything that is not mentioned in the inclusions</li></ul>', 'facility_images/OqvCmFQUaWOFmfKLj4gtKbBbX2OVRUzYVHZ9ppsV.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-22 04:14:44', '2025-03-22 04:14:44', '14'),
(328, 249, 5, 'Description', '<p>Sundarbans is the largest mangrove forest in the world and a natural world heritage listed by UNESCO. This mangrove forest hosts an amazing faunal &amp; floral diversity, including the probably largest remaining population of Royal Bengal tigers, the endangered estuarine crocodile, Ganges River dolphins as well as an astounding variety of birds. Join our luxurious cruise and explore this intricate maze of tidal waterways, a natural treasure of Bangladesh.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Food Menu</strong></p><p>Day 1</p><p>Welcome Juice: Orange Juice</p><p>Breakfast: Bread, Butter, Jam, Honey, Boiled Egg, Banana, Shemai, Tea/Coffee</p><p>Morning Snacks: Fruit Cake, Apple, Tea/Coffee</p><p>Lunch: Plain Rice, Shak Bhaji, Chingri Bhorta, Parsha Fish Fry, Mutton/ Beef Rezala with chui jhal, Special Green Salad, Mineral Water, yoghurt.</p><p>Evening Snacks: Vegetable Spring Roll/Puri, Tea/Coffee</p><p>Dinner: Chicken Corn Soup/Chicken vegetable soup, chicken/egg fired rice,</p><p>fried prawn, special mixed vegetables, soft drinks (250 ml), sweets, mineral water.</p><p>Day 2</p><p>Early Morning Snacks: Biscuits, Muri, Tea/Coffee</p><p>Breakfast: Bhuna Khichuri, Egg curry, Begun Bhaji, achar, green salad, tea/coffee</p><p>Morning Snacks (1): Orange, Biscuit, Mineral Water</p><p>Morning Snacks (2): Green Coconut water</p><p>Lunch: Plain rice, Egg and alu bhorta, Lau chingri, rupchanda fry, chicken roast, daal butter fry, mixed salad, mineral water, sweets.</p><p>Evening Snacks: vegetable pakora, tea/coffee</p><p>Dinner: Porota/Luchi, Mixed Fried Rice, Fish BBQ, Chicken BBQ, Duck Rezala with potato, salad, soft drinks, mineral water, Russian salad</p><p>Day 3:</p><p>Early morning snacks: Biscuit, muri, tea/coffee</p><p>Breakfast: Porota/chapati, mixed vegetables, egg omelets, chicken daal, shuji.</p><p>Morning Snacks: Kheer payesh, tea/coffee</p><p>Lunch: Plain rice, mixed vegetables, egg korma, bagda prawn fry, chicken roast, salad, soft drinks (250ml) mineral water, fruit cocktail</p><p>Evening Snacks: Egg chowmin, tea/coffee</p>', 'facility_images/YOQ78Gpgn8Y0eglHB6x4G4TqegyFw64oW7vt4V9o.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-22 04:15:22', '2025-03-22 04:15:22', '15');
