(329, 249, 6, 'Additional information', '<ul><li><strong>Additional charges will be applied as permit fee for foreigner/non Bangladeshi traveler as per government regulation.</strong></li><li>National ID card to be provided on booking.</li><li>All mentioned durations and activities are subject to change depending on tide, weather and safety conditions.</li><li>The tour operator will responsible for the operation of the tours and excursions as mentioned under the normal situation. So, for personal accident, sickness, loss of baggage during the tour, delay or cancellation of air flight, any political problem resulting in an unusual situation to conduct a tour, etc. we shall not be directly responsible. While the tour operator will responsible for extending all possible assistance in overcoming those problems, but the guest must pay any extra cost incurred due to these problems.</li><li>The time mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather condition, tides in the river, convenience of the travelers and other unavoidable circumstances. Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator/host/organizer in case of such circumstance.</li><li>The travelers are requested to contact with the tour operator/host/organizer incase they face any kind of trouble/problem during the tour.</li><li>No alcohol will be available for sale on board.</li><li>No phone signal works inside the deeper forest. But at some point, you will get a phone signal to call the emergency. If you use Bangladeshi TeleTalk SIM, we’ll get better coverage in a remote area like Kotka.<br><br><strong>Requirements:</strong></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Must bring National ID card</li><li>Valid permission for drone and professional camera from respective authorities</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'facility_images/6A55e6UydhfeG8TDbiOLsw41Ly20mjAbZtqEhPCz.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-22 04:15:59', '2025-03-22 04:15:59', '14'),
(330, 249, 7, 'Travel tips', '<p><strong>Guidelines While on the Cruise:</strong></p><ol><li>Dispose of Waste Properly: Please refrain from dropping any items into the water or within the jungle. Utilize the designated \"Bin\" on the boat to dispose of waste responsibly.</li><li>Fire Safety: Smoking and any form of fire are strictly prohibited within the cabins for the safety of all passengers.</li><li>Conservation of Resources: Please use water and electricity efficiently, considering the limited resources available during the cruise.</li><li>Timely Meals: To ensure smooth operations, kindly adhere to meal timings.</li><li>Child Supervision: Keep a watchful eye on your children to ensure their safety and enjoyment.</li><li>Valuables Protection: Take necessary precautions to safeguard your valuables during the journey.</li><li>Liability Notice: Understand that GoZayaan or the tour operator will not be held responsible for accidents, theft, loss, or damages. Travelers are encouraged to take necessary precautions.</li><li>Booking Changes: If you need to change your booking date or cancel, it\'s imperative to inform the tour operator in advance.</li><li>Preserving the Environment: Littering is strictly prohibited in the river, along the shore, and at tourist spots. Please maintain the cleanliness of these areas.</li><li>Respect for Nature: Avoid making noise, disturbing animals, or damaging plant life, respecting the natural ecosystem.</li><li>Seat/Cabin Adjustments: In certain situations, the authorities might need to modify seat or cabin assignments for operational reasons.</li><li>Forest Regulations: Travelers are kindly requested to adhere to the rules and regulations of the forest authorities.</li></ol><p><strong>Guidelines While in the Jungle:</strong></p><ol><li>Stay Together: Always remain in a group while inside the jungle. Avoid solitary exploration for safety reasons.</li><li>Flora and Fauna: Refrain from causing harm to plants and animals in the forest. Please respect their natural habitat.</li><li>Communication: If you encounter any issues, communicate exclusively with your assigned tour guide, who is trained to handle various situations.</li><li>Appropriate Attire: Opt for jungle-friendly attire, avoiding bright colors that might disturb the natural environment.</li><li>Minimize Scents: Avoid using perfumes while in the jungle, as scents can imitate wildlife and disrupt their behavior.</li><li>Respecting the Reserve: Recognize that the Sundarbans is a reserved forest without human habitation. In unforeseen circumstances, remain calm and follow the guide\'s instructions to manage the situation effectively.</li></ol><p>By adhering to these guidelines, you\'ll contribute to the safety of all passengers, the preservation of the environment, and the enjoyment of an enriching experience in the mesmerizing Sundarbans.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Preparing for a 3-day tour in the Sundarbans requires packing thoughtfully to ensure your comfort, safety, and enjoyment. Here\'s a list of essentials you should consider taking:</p><p>Clothing:</p><ul><li>Lightweight shirts and pants</li><li>Long-sleeved shirts</li><li>Comfortable walking shoes</li><li>Sandals or water shoes</li><li>Hat or cap</li><li>Rain jacket or poncho</li></ul><p>Personal Items:</p><ul><li>Identification documents</li><li>Medications</li><li>Insect repellent</li><li>Sunscreen</li><li>Personal hygiene items</li></ul><p>Accessories:</p><ul><li>Sunglasses</li><li>Binoculars</li><li>Camera</li><li>Power bank</li></ul><p>Miscellaneous:</p><ul><li>Cash money</li><li>Water bottle</li><li>Backpack or daypack</li><li>Swimsuit (if applicable)</li><li>Flashlight or headlamp</li><li>Travel towel</li></ul><p>Electronics:</p><ul><li>Mobile phone</li><li>Charger cables</li><li>Camera gear</li></ul><p>Important Documents:</p><ul><li>Passport or ID</li><li>Booking confirmation</li><li>Emergency contact information</li></ul><p>Eco-Friendly Items:</p><ul><li>Reusable water bottle</li><li>Reusable utensils and containers</li></ul><p>Remember to tailor the list to your specific needs and the time of year you\'ll be visiting the Sundarbans.</p>', 'facility_images/UDVxKgm7qEh4dByPj084JT09lgL0Y8xiZGAl5Avq.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-22 04:16:42', '2025-03-22 04:16:42', '13'),
