(358, 257, 5, NULL, '<p>Step into the extraordinary world of the Sundarbans, a sprawling expanse of wonder that stands as the largest mangrove forest on the globe. Its awe-inspiring beauty has earned it a distinguished spot on UNESCO\'s list of natural world heritage sites.</p><p>This enchanting mangrove forest is a sanctuary of unparalleled diversity, where the tapestry of life weaves together in stunning harmony. Here, amidst the intertwining roots and lush greenery, you\'ll find a captivating array of fauna and flora. It\'s home to what is believed to be the largest surviving population of the majestic Royal Bengal tigers, a testament to nature\'s magnificence. The elusive estuarine crocodile, the enchanting Ganges River dolphins, and a myriad of vibrant bird species complete the ensemble of life that calls this forest home.</p><p>Picture yourself aboard our luxurious cruise, an experience that seamlessly blends opulence and discovery. As you navigate this intricate maze of tidal waterways, every twist and turn reveals a new facet of this natural gem nestled within Bangladesh\'s heart. The journey is as much a destination as the forest itself.</p><p>Indulge in the symphony of senses as you explore the diverse ecosystems, from the dense mangrove thickets to the tranquil waterways. With each moment, you\'ll be immersed in the spellbinding allure that the Sundarbans effortlessly casts. And when it\'s time to savor a moment of reprieve, our cruise promises not only comfort but culinary delights, with a tantalizing array of full-board meals to satiate your appetite for both adventure and fine dining.</p><p>This is your chance to be a part of something truly remarkable – a voyage into the heart of a natural treasure, where every glimpse is a glimpse into the timeless rhythm of nature\'s dance. Join us in discovering the Sundarbans, where the extraordinary is simply the ordinary.&nbsp;</p>', 'facility_images/9mcahOsa9259sRz9MmKvHfDmHxO6yObStFrFfDlf.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-24 06:27:01', '2025-03-24 06:27:01', '14'),
(359, 257, 6, NULL, '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Additional charges will be applied as permit fees for foreigners and non-Bangladeshi travelers as per government regulation.</li><li>A national ID card must be provided on booking. All mentioned durations and activities are subject to change depending on tide, weather, and safety conditions.</li><li>The tour operator will be responsible for the operation of the tours and excursions as mentioned under the normal situation. So, for personal accidents, sickness, loss of baggage during the tour, delay or cancellation of an air flight, any political problem resulting in an unusual situation to conduct a tour, etc, GoZayaan shall not be directly responsible.</li><li>While the tour operator will be responsible for extending all possible assistance in overcoming those problems, the guest must pay any extra cost incurred due to these problems.</li><li>The times mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather conditions, tides in the river, the convenience of the travelers, and other unavoidable circumstances.</li><li>Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator, host, or organizer in such circumstances.</li><li>The travelers are requested to contact the tour operator, host, or organizer in case they face any kind of trouble or problem during the tour.</li><li>No alcohol will be available for sale on board.</li><li>No phone signal works inside the deeper forest. But at some point, you will get a phone signal to call the emergency number.</li><li>If you use a Bangladeshi TeleTalk SIM, we’ll get better coverage in a remote area like Kotka.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Must bring National ID card</li><li>Valid permission for drone and professional camera from respective authorities</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'facility_images/D6T7MLPXRDRL4t8NvijNrL9ePlnYA8otOVYPaVmg.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-03-24 06:27:35', '2025-03-24 06:27:35', '18');
