(446, 264, 5, NULL, '<p>Step into the extraordinary world of the Sundarbans, a sprawling expanse of wonder that stands as the largest mangrove forest on the globe. Its awe-inspiring beauty has earned it a distinguished spot on UNESCO\'s list of natural world heritage sites.</p><p>This enchanting mangrove forest is a sanctuary of unparalleled diversity, where the tapestry of life weaves together in stunning harmony. Here, amidst the intertwining roots and lush greenery, you\'ll find a captivating array of fauna and flora. It\'s home to what is believed to be the largest surviving population of the majestic Royal Bengal tigers, a testament to nature\'s magnificence. The elusive estuarine crocodile, the enchanting Ganges River dolphins, and a myriad of vibrant bird species complete the ensemble of life that calls this forest home.</p><p>Picture yourself aboard our luxurious cruise, an experience that seamlessly blends opulence and discovery. As you navigate this intricate maze of tidal waterways, every twist and turn reveals a new facet of this natural gem nestled within Bangladesh\'s heart. The journey is as much a destination as the forest itself.</p><p>Indulge in the symphony of senses as you explore the diverse ecosystems, from the dense mangrove thickets to the tranquil waterways. With each moment, you\'ll be immersed in the spellbinding allure that the Sundarbans effortlessly casts. And when it\'s time to savor a moment of reprieve, our cruise promises not only comfort but culinary delights, with a tantalizing array of full-board meals to satiate your appetite for both adventure and fine dining.</p><p>This is your chance to be a part of something truly remarkable – a voyage into the heart of a natural treasure, where every glimpse is a glimpse into the timeless rhythm of nature\'s dance. Join us in discovering the Sundarbans, where the extraordinary is simply the ordinary.&nbsp;</p>', 'facility_images/UZxfNJ897FCXbxD5NFB6hp7RTAw7mH3SvWx5oqoK.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-04-08 04:50:39', '2025-04-08 04:50:39', '14'),
(447, 264, 6, NULL, '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Additional charges will be applied as permit fees for foreigners and non-Bangladeshi travelers as per government regulation.</li><li>A national ID card must be provided on booking. All mentioned durations and activities are subject to change depending on tide, weather, and safety conditions.</li><li>The tour operator will be responsible for the operation of the tours and excursions as mentioned under the normal situation. So, for personal accidents, sickness, loss of baggage during the tour, delay or cancellation of an air flight, any political problem resulting in an unusual situation to conduct a tour, etc, GoZayaan shall not be directly responsible.</li><li>While the tour operator will be responsible for extending all possible assistance in overcoming those problems, the guest must pay any extra cost incurred due to these problems.</li><li>The times mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather conditions, tides in the river, the convenience of the travelers, and other unavoidable circumstances.</li><li>Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator, host, or organizer in such circumstances.</li><li>The travelers are requested to contact the tour operator, host, or organizer in case they face any kind of trouble or problem during the tour.</li><li>No alcohol will be available for sale on board.</li><li>No phone signal works inside the deeper forest. But at some point, you will get a phone signal to call the emergency number.</li><li>If you use a Bangladeshi TeleTalk SIM, we’ll get better coverage in a remote area like Kotka.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Must bring National ID card</li><li>Valid permission for drone and professional camera from respective authorities</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'facility_images/78y9k9UpoMQLTxi03SULpNNw9oYFZi66VU7IaYgJ.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-04-08 04:52:05', '2025-04-08 04:52:05', '12'),
(448, 264, 7, NULL, '<ol><li>jungle. Utilize the designated \"Bin\" on the boat to dispose of waste responsibly.</li><li>Fire Safety: Smoking and any form of fire are strictly prohibited within the cabins for the safety of all passengers.</li><li>Conservation of Resources: Please use water and electricity efficiently, considering the limited resources available during the cruise.</li><li>Timely Meals: To ensure smooth operations, kindly adhere to meal timings.</li><li>Child Supervision: Keep a watchful eye on your children to ensure their safety and enjoyment.</li><li>Valuables Protection: Take necessary precautions to safeguard your valuables during the journey.</li><li>Liability Notice: Understand that GoZayaan or the tour operator will not be held responsible for accidents, theft, loss, or damages. Travelers are encouraged to take necessary precautions.</li><li>Booking Changes: If you need to change your booking date or cancel, it\'s imperative to inform the tour operator in advance.</li><li>Preserving the Environment: Littering is strictly prohibited in the river, along the shore, and at tourist spots. Please maintain the cleanliness of these areas.</li><li>Respect for Nature: Avoid making noise, disturbing animals, or damaging plant life, respecting the natural ecosystem.</li><li>Seat/Cabin Adjustments: In certain situations, the authorities might need to modify seat or cabin assignments for operational reasons.</li><li>Forest Regulations: Travelers are kindly requested to adhere to the rules and regulations of the forest authorities.</li></ol><p><strong>Guidelines While in the Jungle:</strong></p><ol><li>Stay Together: Always remain in a group while inside the jungle. Avoid solitary exploration for safety reasons.</li><li>Flora and Fauna: Refrain from causing harm to plants and animals in the forest. Please respect their natural habitat.</li><li>Communication: If you encounter any issues, communicate exclusively with your assigned tour guide, who is trained to handle various situations.</li><li>Appropriate Attire: Opt for jungle-friendly attire, avoiding bright colors that might disturb the natural environment.</li><li>Minimize Scents: Avoid using perfumes while in the jungle, as scents can imitate wildlife and disrupt their behavior.</li><li>Respecting the Reserve: Recognize that the Sundarbans is a reserved forest without human habitation. In unforeseen circumstances, remain calm and follow the guide\'s instructions to manage the situation effectively.</li></ol><p>By adhering to these guidelines, you\'ll contribute to the safety of all passengers, the preservation of the environment, and the enjoyment of an enriching experience in the mesmerizing Sundarbans.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Preparing for a 3-day tour in the Sundarbans requires packing thoughtfully to ensure your comfort, safety, and enjoyment. Here\'s a list of essentials you should consider taking:</p><p>Clothing:</p><ul><li>Lightweight shirts and pants</li><li>Long-sleeved shirts</li><li>Comfortable walking shoes</li><li>Sandals or water shoes</li><li>Hat or cap</li><li>Rain jacket or poncho</li></ul><p>Personal Items:</p><ul><li>Identification documents</li><li>Medications</li><li>Insect repellent</li><li>Sunscreen</li><li>Personal hygiene items</li></ul><p>Accessories:</p><ul><li>Sunglasses</li><li>Binoculars</li><li>Camera</li><li>Power bank</li></ul><p>Miscellaneous:</p><ul><li>Cash money</li><li>Water bottle</li><li>Backpack or daypack</li><li>Swimsuit (if applicable)</li><li>Flashlight or headlamp</li><li>Travel towel</li></ul><p>Electronics:</p><ul><li>Mobile phone</li><li>Charger cables</li><li>Camera gear</li></ul><p>Important Documents:</p><ul><li>Passport or ID</li><li>Booking confirmation</li><li>Emergency contact information</li></ul><p>Eco-Friendly Items:</p><ul><li>Reusable water bottle</li><li>Reusable utensils and containers</li></ul><p>Remember to tailor the list to your specific needs and the time of year you\'ll be visiting the Sundarban</p>', 