(478, 268, 5, NULL, '<p>Sundarbans is the largest mangrove forest in the world and a natural world heritage listed by UNESCO. This mangrove forest hosts an amazing faunal &amp; floral diversity, including the probably largest remaining population of Royal Bengal tigers, the endangered estuarine crocodile, Ganges River dolphins as well as an astounding variety of birds. Join our luxurious cruise and explore this intricate maze of tidal waterways, a natural treasure of Bangladesh.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>FOOD MENU :&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>1st Day:</strong></p><p><strong>Breakfast:</strong> Paratha, Vegetables, Mug Dal bhuna, Egg fry, tea/Coffee.</p><p><strong>Morning Snacks:</strong> Fruit cake, tea/coffee.</p><p><strong>Lunch:</strong> White rice, green prawns, vetki fish (coral), duck meat bharta, dal, Sweets, Salad.</p><p><strong>Evening Snacks:</strong> French Fry &amp; Soup.</p><p><strong>Dinner:</strong> Egg fried rice, chicken fry, fried shrimp, Chinese vegetables, salad, soft drinks.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2nd Day:&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Breakfast:</strong> Bhuna khichuri, sea fish, brinjal vaji, egg curry, pickles, salad, tea/coffee.</p><p><strong>Morning Snacks:</strong> Sarabat, Guava, Tea/Coffee</p><p><strong>Lunch:</strong> White rice, bharta, gourd prawns, chicken curry, dal, salad, dessert.</p><p><strong>Evening Snacks:</strong> Puri/Pakura, tea/coffee.</p><p><strong>Dinner:</strong> Porata, Chicken Bar-b-fish Bar-b-q, Booter Dal Buna, Russian Salad, Cold Drinks.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>3rd Day:</strong></p><p><strong>Breakfast:</strong> Paratha, vegetables, Gorur kolija bhuna, Shuji halwa, tea/coffee.</p><p><strong>Morning Snacks:</strong> Fruit, tea/coffee.</p><p><strong>Lunch:</strong> Plain rice, Rupchada fish, mutton, vharta, dal salad, Sweet Card</p><p><strong>Evening Snacks:</strong> Nodols &amp;&nbsp;tea/coffee.</p>', 'facility_images/eYhx5F9EtfMFuHcB7slE4GvD7cnKW6CXEpUjKRdp.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-04-08 09:38:53', '2025-04-08 09:38:53', '17'),
(479, 268, 6, NULL, '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>government regulation.</strong></li><li>National ID card to be provided on booking.</li><li>All mentioned durations and activities are subject to change depending on tide, weather and safety conditions.</li><li>The tour operator will responsible for the operation of the tours and excursions as mentioned under the normal situation. So, for personal accident, sickness, loss of baggage during the tour, delay or cancellation of air flight, any political problem resulting in an unusual situation to conduct a tour, etc. we shall not be directly responsible. While the tour operator will responsible for extending all possible assistance in overcoming those problems, but the guest must pay any extra cost incurred due to these problems.</li><li>The time mentioned in the itinerary is subject to change due to weather conditions, tides in the river, the convenience of the travelers, and other unavoidable circumstances. Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator/host/organizer in case of such circumstances.</li><li>The travelers are requested to contact the tour operator/host/organizer in case they face any kind of trouble/problem during the tour.</li><li>No alcohol will be available for sale onboard.</li><li>No phone signal works inside the deeper forest. But at some point, you will get a phone signal to call the emergency. If you use Bangladeshi TeleTalk SIM, we’ll get better coverage in a remote area like Kotka.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Must bring national ID card</li><li>Valid permission for drone and professional camera from respective authorities</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'facility_images/abNef09ojyBlnkJwGS3Mul1X00XVFyP4Lgqozr07.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-04-08 09:39:24', '2025-04-08 09:39:24', '17');
