n any of the previous visas.</p><p><strong>3.06</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Accommodation :</strong></p><p>Hotel reservation or inviter\'s residence address for the whole duration of the intended stay in Austria.</p><p><strong>3.07</strong></p><p><strong>Invitation letter (if any):</strong></p><p>An original copy of the invitation letter from the company or organization or from friends and family with evidence. It should include the intended stay.</p><p><strong>3.08</strong></p><p><strong>Forwarding Letter :</strong></p><p>The applicant\'s name, designation, passport number, purpose, and duration of the visa.</p><p><strong>3.09</strong></p><p><strong>Financial Documents :</strong></p><p>*Personal Bank Statement of the last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency certificate.<br>*TIN certificate<br>*Income Tax certificate (Last 2 years), Tax Return (ITR)</p><p><strong>3.10</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Occupation and Identiy :</strong></p><p>*Visiting Card<br>*If the applicant is a doctor, then he will show a BMDC certificate; If he is a lawyer, then he will have to show a Bar Council certificate; and others have to prove their occupation from their respective autonomous bodies.<br>*Valid Passport, NID, photo, and birth certificate.</p><p><strong>3.11</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of civil status :</strong></p><p>*Marriage Certificate - if married (also NIkah Nama both in Bangla &amp; English,for Muslim Marriage in A4 size photocopy)<br>*Divorce Certificate - (talak nama) if applicable.<br>*Death certificate - if applicable.<br>*Birth certificate of children - if applicable.</p><p><strong>3.12</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents :</strong></p><p>For minors below the age of 18, proof of legal parenthood (if applicable):<br>*copy of either a birth certificate or proof of adoption (if adopted).<br>*custody decree in case parents are divorced or death certificate of parents (if applicable).<br>*\'Letter of Consent\' from the legal guardian, including his/her passport copy legalized by a notary public. (This is only required in cases where the legal guardian is not present during the Visa appointment.)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Others :</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>4.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport :</strong></p><p>A valid passport that is original and at least 3/6 months validity is essential. Moreover,<br>*the passport should not be older than 10years.<br>*the passport must have at least two blank pages. *copies of your previous Schengen Visas (if applicable)<br>Note: All previous passports and Visa\'s are required (if any).</p><p><strong>4.02</strong></p><p><strong>A Cover Letter :</strong></p><p>Covering Letter from applicant name, designation, Passport Number, purpose and outlining who will be responsible for the full costs of the trip – travel, accommodation, expenses etc. Addressed to - The Visa Officer,Embassy of Austria,Dhaka.</p><p><strong>4.03</strong></p><p><strong>Round trip flight itinerary :</strong></p><p>Containing the dates and flight numbers specifying entry &amp; exit from Austria.</p><p><strong>4.04</strong></p><p><strong>Travel Insurance :</strong></p><p>Insurance must be valid for the whole Schengen area. The Insurance must cover the repatriation costs up to 30,000 Euros. The Insurance must fully cover the whole period of stay within the Schengen area.<br>*The conditions must be stated either on the insurance document or on a separate confirmation letter.</p><p><strong>4.05</strong></p><p><strong>Photo Specification :</strong></p><p>Passport sized photograph (3.5cm by 4.5cm)<br>*The photo should be a recent whole face capture with a white background.<br>*Neutral face expression (No smile &amp; mouth closed)<br><br>Please Note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p><p><strong>4.06</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Accommodation :</strong></p><p>Hotel reservation or inviter\'s residence address for the whole duration of the intended stay in Austria.</p><p><strong>4.07</strong></p><p><strong>Invitation letter(if any)</strong></p><p>An original copy of the invitation letter from the company or organization or from friends and family with evidence. It should include the intended stay.</p><p><strong>4.08</strong></p><p><strong>Forwarding Letter :</strong></p><p>The applicant\'s name, designation, passport number, purpose, and duration of the visa.</p><p><strong>4.09</strong></p><p><strong>Financial Documents :</strong></p><p>*Personal Bank Statement of the last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency certificate.<br>*TIN certificate<br>*Income Tax Certificate (Last 2 years), Tax Return (ITR)</p><p><strong>4.10</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Occupation and Identiy :</strong></p><p>*Valid Passport, NID, photo, and birth certificate.<br>*Visa request letter from the educational institute or student card/evidence of school enrollment (if student)</p><p><strong>4.11</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of civil status :</strong></p><p>*Marriage Certificate - if married (also NIkah Nama both in Bangla &amp; English,for Muslim Marriage in A4 size photocopy)<br>*Divorce Certificate - (talak nama) if applicable.<br>*Death certificate - if applicable.<br>*Birth certificate of children - if applicable.</p><p><strong>4.12</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents :</strong></p><p>For minors below the age of 18, proof of legal parenthood (if applicable):<br>*copy of either a birth certificate or proof of adoption (if adopted).<br>*custody decree in case parents are divorced or death certificate of parents (if applicable).<br>*\'Letter of Consent\' from the legal guardian, including his/her passport copy legalized by a notary public. (This is only required in cases where the legal guardian is not present during the Visa appointment.)</p>', 'facility_images/QtyqgmAV3T33IlcwZTYhVvQkXveJUS2wKN5BTH4M.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-05-03 05:24:05', '2025-05-03 05:24:05', NULL),
