(633, 339, NULL, 'Required Documents for Visa', '<p><strong>Eligibility to Apply for Visa</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Any Bangladeshi Nationals are Eligible to Apply for China Tourist Visa (having a valid MRP / E-Passport with at least 6 months validity) subject to provide some required Documents.<br>Also Applicant should,<br>• be a genuine visitor<br>• have enough funds to support his/her stay and leave</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Documents Requirements</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>1. Service Holder</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>1.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>Original Passport with validity of minimum Seventh months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>a) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>b) Attach all your old passports (if any).<br>c) If any visa request was refused, details of original letter issued by the authorities of that country would be preferred.</p><p><strong>1.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo Specification</strong></p><p>Two recent passport size photographs with matt paper 60%-80% face coverage, white background and without border (Size: 33 mm x 48 mm).<br>Please Note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p><p><strong>1.03</strong></p><p><strong>Forwarding Letter</strong></p><p>NOC from the applicant\'s company authority on the company\'s letterhead stating the applicant\'s name, designation, passport number, purpose, and duration of the visa.<br>**The NOC letter is highly important for your Schengen visa application.(Pay slips should be included in it.</p><p><strong>1.04</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants/Sponsors Proof of Occupation</strong></p><p>*Office ID Card/Visiting Card<br>*Company Letter Pad : A letter from your employer on company letterhead, with contact details, stating that a leave of absence has been granted, the purpose and duration of the trip, and that you will be returning to your current job (if you are a job holder).<br>*Salary slips for the last 6 months<br>*Valid Passport, NID, Photo, and Birth certificate.</p><p><strong>1.05</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants/Sponsors Financials Proof</strong></p><p>*Personal Bank Statement of the last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency Certificate<br>*TIN certificate<br>*Income Tax certificate (Last 2 years), Tax Return (ITR)</p><p><strong>1.06</strong></p><p><strong>Covering-Letter</strong></p><p>Covering Letter from applicant name, designation, Passport Number, purpose and outlining who will be responsible for the full costs of the trip – travel, accommodation, expenses etc. Addressed to – The Visa Officer, Embassy of China, Dhaka.</p><p><strong>1.07</strong></p><p><strong>Flight and hotel reservations</strong></p><p>Valid Flight and Hotel bookings or the inviter\'s residence address is required</p><p><strong>1.08</strong></p><p><strong>Invitation Letter (If Any)</strong></p><p>An invitation letter issued by a relevant entity approved by the Local Government of China (Invitation Letter of Duly Authorized Unit)</p><p><strong>1.09</strong></p><p><strong>Covid-19 Vaccine Certificate</strong></p><p>Covid-19 Vaccine certificate is required</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>2. Business Person</strong></h2><p><strong>2.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>Original Passport with validity of minimum Seventh months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>a) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>b) Attach all your old passports (if any).<br>c) If any visa request was refused, details of original letter issued by the authorities of that country would be preferred.</p><p><strong>2.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo Specification</strong></p><p>Two recent passport size photographs with matt paper 60%-80% face coverage, white background and without border (Size: 33 mm x 48 mm).<br>Please Note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scan