(637, 341, NULL, 'Required Documents for Visa', '<p><strong>Eligibility to Apply for Visa</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Any Bangladeshi Nationals are Eligible to Apply for Denmark Tourist Visa (having a valid MRP / E-Passport with at least 6 months validity) subject to provide some required Documents.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Documents Requirements</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>1. Service Holder</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>1.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a. Passport with at least two blank pages, valid for at least 3 months after leaving the Schengen territory.<br>b. All previous passports (photocopy of bio page and of any previous Schengen, UK, Australian or US visas).</p><p><strong>1.02</strong></p><p><strong>Cover Letter and Tour Plan</strong></p><p>In a cover letter, applicants have to mention the cost and purpose of the visit. In a tour plan, the Travel Itinerary and places to be visited must be mentioned.</p><p><strong>1.03</strong></p><p><strong>Photo Specification</strong></p><p>A recent (6-month-old) two-color photo with a white background is necessary. Photos format should be in ICAO standard (3.5 cm x 4.5 cm). The photograph should be printed on matt/semi-matt paper, and without border.</p><p><strong>1.04</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants / Sponsors Proof of Occupation and Identity</strong></p><p>*Office ID Card/Visiting Card<br>*Company Letter Pad : A letter from your employer on company letterhead, with contact details, stating that a leave of absence has been granted, the purpose and duration of the trip, and that you will be returning to your current job (if you are a job holder).<br>*Salary slips for the last 6 months<br>*Valid Passport, NID, Photo, and Birth certificate.</p><p><strong>1.05</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants / Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>*Personal Bank Statement of the last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency certificate.<br>*TIN certificate<br>*Income Tax certificate (Last 2 years), Tax Return (ITR)</p><p><strong>1.06</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of civil status</strong></p><p>Marriage Certificate – if married (also Nikah Nama both in Bangla and English, for Muslim marriage in<br>A4 size Photocopy)<br>a. Divorce certificate (“talak namah”) – if applicable<br>b. Death Certificate – if applicable<br>c. Birth Certificate of your children –if applicable</p><p><strong>1.07</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>For minors below the age of 18 (if applicable) – proving legal parenthood:<br>a. Copy of either birth certificate/proof of adoption/custody decree in case parents are divorced.<br>b. If applicable - the death certificate of parent ( Danish or English translation is required).<br>c. “Letter of consent” from legal guardian, including his/her passport copy – legalized by a notary public<br>(only required in cases the legal guardian is not present during the visa appointment)</p><p><strong>1.08</strong></p><p><strong>Travel Insurance</strong></p><p>Insurance must be valid for the whole Schengen area. The Insurance must cover the repatriation costs up to 30,000 Euros. The Insurance must fully cover the whole period of stay within the Schengen area.<br>*The conditions must be stated either on the insurance document or on a separate confirmation letter.</p><p><strong>1.09</strong></p><p><strong>Flight and hotel reservation</strong></p><p>Valid round trip Air Ticket confirmation and Hotel confirmation for the whole duration of the stay, or other documents proving accommodation is required.</p><p><strong>1.10</strong></p><p><strong>Forwarding-Letter</strong></p><p>NOC from the applicant\'s company authority on the company\'s letterhead stating the applicant\'s name, designation, passport number, purpose, and duration of the visa.<br>**The NOC letter is highly important for your Schengen visa application.(Pay slips should be included in it.)</p><p><strong>1.11</strong></p><p><strong>Invitation Letter (If Any)</strong></p><p>An original copy of Invitation letter from company/ Organization or Friends and Family with evidence.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>2. Business Person</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a. Passport with at least two blank pages, valid for at least 3 months after leaving the Schengen territory.<br>b. All previous passports (photocopy of bio page and of any previous Schengen, UK, Australian or US visas).</p><p><strong>2.02</strong></p><p><strong>Cover Letter and Tour Plan</strong></p><p>In a cover letter, applicants have to mention the cost and purpose of the visit. In a tour plan, the Travel Itinerary and places to be visited must be mentioned.</p><p><strong>2.03</strong></p><p><strong>Photo Specification</strong></p><p>A recent (6-month-old) two-color photo with a white background is necessary. Photos format should be in ICAO standard (3.5 cm x 4.5 cm). The photograph should be printed on matt/semi-matt paper, and without border.</p><p><strong>2.04</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants / Sponsors Proof of Occupation and Identity</strong></p><p>*Company memorandum.<br>*Visiting card.<br>*Updated Trade License<br>*Valid Passport copy, NID, Photo, Birth certificate.</p><p><strong>2.05</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants / Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>a. Personal bank Statement of Last Six Months and Bank Solvency Certificate.<br>b. Company bank Statement of Last Six Months and Bank Solvency Certificate (if business).<br>b. TIN certificate<br>c. Income Tax Certificate, Tax Return (Last 02 Years)<br>Income Tax Certificate of Company (In Case of Business Person).</p><p><strong>2.06</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of civil status</strong></p><p>Marriage Certificate – if married (also Nikah Nama both in Bangla and English, for Muslim marriage in<br>A4 size Photocopy)<br>a. Divorce certificate (“talak namah”) – if applicable<br>b. Death Certificate – if applicable<br>c. Birth Certificate of your children –if applicable</p><p><stron