(649, 347, NULL, 'Required Documents for Visa', '<p><strong>Eligibility to Apply for Visa</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Any Bangladeshi Nationals are Eligible to Apply for \'INDIA TOURIST VISA\' (having a valid MRP / E-Passport with at least 6 months validity) subject to provide some required Documents.<br>Also Applicant should,<br>• be a genuine visitor<br>• have enough funds to support his/her stay and leave</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Documents Requirements</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>1. Service Holder</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>1.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a) Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>b) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>c) Attach all your old passports (if any).</p><p><strong>1.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo</strong></p><p>Two recent passport size lab print photographs white background and without border (Size: 2”x 2”)<br>Please Note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p><p><strong>1.03</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Occupation</strong></p><p>a. No Objection Certificate (NOC) from Employer.<br>b. Office ID card<br>c. Visiting Card<br>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>1.04</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>Updated bank statement (last 3 month / 6 months) / endorsement* of foreign currency equivalent to US$150/- per applicant ( Endorsement* should not be older than 1 (one) month at the time of submission), International credit card with running year endorsement in the passport.<br><br>Please Note : Personal Bank Statement for the last six months mentioning the Bank’s name, Bank’s Telephone Number clearly.</p><p><strong>1.05</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Resident</strong></p><p>Utility bills, such as those for electricity, telephone, gas, or water, that are no older than six months. If the applicant resides in a flat, they may also give a copy of the building\'s main bill or a sub bill.</p><p><strong>1.06</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>1. Applicants NID required.<br>2. Birth Certificate required for depended child if the depended wants to apply for the visa also.</p><h2><strong>2. Business Person</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a) Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>b) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>c) Attach all your old passports (if any).</p><p><strong>2.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo</strong></p><p>Two recent passport size lab print photographs white background and without border (Size: 2”x 2”)<br>Please Note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p><p><strong>2.03</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Occupation</strong></p><p>a. Trade license (original notarized English translation and photocopy of the original trade license required) for proprietorship business, Memorandum of Article for limited company if the applicant’s name is not mentioned in the trade license.<br>b. Visiting Card</p><p><strong>2.04</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>Updated bank statement (last 3 month / 6 months) / endorsement* of foreign currency equivalent to US$150/- per applicant ( Endorsement* should not be older than 1 (one) month at the time of submission), International credit card with running year endorsement in the passport.<br><br>Please Note : Company’s or Personal Bank Statement for the last six months mentioning the Bank’s name, Bank’s Telephone Number clearly.</p><p><strong>2.05</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Resident</strong></p><p>Utility bills, such as those for electricity, telephone, gas, or water, that are no older than six months. If the applicant resides in a flat, they may also give a copy of the building\'s main bill or a sub bill.</p><p><strong>2.06</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>1. Applicants NID required.<br>2. Birth Certificate required for depended child if the depended wants to apply for the visa also.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>3. Professionals(Doctor, Engineer, CA etc)</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>3.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a) Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>b) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>c) Attach all your old passports (if any).</p><p><strong>3.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo</strong></p><p>Two recent passport size lab print photographs white background and without border (Size: 2”x 2”)<br>Please Note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p><p><strong>3.03</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Occupation</strong></p><p>a. BMDC certificate or letter from hospital if the applicant is a Doctor,<br>b. A Bar Council Certificate or letter from a law firm if the applicant is a lawyer.<br>c. Visiting Card</p><p><strong>3.04</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>Updated bank statement (last 3 month / 6 months) / endorsement* of foreign currency equivalent to US$150/- per applicant ( Endorsement* should not be older than 1 (one) month at the time of submission), International credit card with running year endorsement in the passport.<br><br>Please Note : Personal Bank Statement for the last six months mentioning the Bank’s name, Bank’s Telephone Number clearly.</p><p><strong>3.05</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Resident</strong></p><p>Utility bills, such as those for electricity, telephone, gas, or water, that are no older than six months. If the applicant resides in a flat, they may also give a copy of the building\'s main bill or a sub bill.</p><p><strong>3.06</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>1. Applicants NID required.<br>2. Birth Certificate required for depended child if the depended wants to apply for the visa also.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>4. Others</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>4.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a) Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>b) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>c) Attach all your old passports (if any).</p><p><strong>4.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo</strong></p><p>Two recent passport size lab print photographs white background and without border (Size: 2”x 2”)<br>Please Note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p><p><strong>4.03</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Occupation</strong></p><p>A recommendation letter from the school / university or student ID card /evidence of school / university enrolment) if the applicant is a student.</p><p><strong>4.04</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>Updated bank statement (last 3 month / 6 months) / endorsement* of foreign currency equivalent to US$150/- per applicant ( Endorsement* should not be older than 1 (one) month at the time of submission), International credit card with running year endorsement in the passport.<br><br>Please Note : Personal Bank Statement for the last six months mentioning the Bank’s name, Bank’s Telephone Number clearly.</p><p><strong>4.05</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of Resident</strong></p><p>Utility bills, such as those for electricity, telephone, gas, or water, that are no older than six months. If the applicant resides in a flat, they may also give a copy of the building\'s main bill or a sub bill.</p><p><strong>4.06</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>1. Applicants NID required.<br>2. Birth Certificate required for depended child if the depended wants to apply for the visa also.</p>', 'facility_images/Ys4rfaIYgzC5kDD7Eoy8R4LIRUQ5TJxj6MdjVb3E.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-05-03 12:04:29', '2025-05-03 12:04:29', NULL),
