(651, 348, NULL, 'Required Documents for Visa', '<p><strong>Eligibility to Apply for Visa</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Any Bangladeshi Nationals are Eligible to Apply for Latvia Tourist Visa (having a valid MRP / E-Passport with at least 6 months validity) subject to provide some required Documents.<br>Also Applicant should,<br>• be a genuine visitor<br>• have enough funds to support his/her stay and leave</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Documents Requirements</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>1. Service Holder</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>1.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>A valid passport that is original and at least Three / six months validity is essential. Moreover, the passport must have at least two blank pages.<br>Note: All previous passports and Visa\'s are required (if any).</p><p><strong>1.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo Specification</strong></p><p>Passport sized photographs (3.5 cm x 4.5cm)<br>a. Should not be older than 6 months.<br>b. A frontal view of the face covering 70-80% (32-26mm) of the biometric photo.<br>c. A uniform and white background.<br>d. Clear facial features<br>e. Head coverings are only accepted for religious reasons.<br>Do not glue or staple the pictures to the application form.</p><p><strong>1.03</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants/Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>*Personal Bank Statement of the last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency certificate.<br>*TIN certificate<br>*Income Tax certificate (Last 2 years), Tax Return (ITR)</p><p><strong>1.04</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants/Sponsors Proof of Occupation and Identity</strong></p><p>*Office ID Card/Visiting Card<br>*Company Letter Pad: A letter from your employer on company letterhead, with contact details, stating that a leave of absence has been granted, the purpose and duration of the trip, and that you will be returning to your current job (if you are a job holder).<br>*Salary slips for the last 6 months<br>*Valid Passport, NID, Photo, and Birth certificate.</p><p><strong>1.05</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of civil status</strong></p><p>Marriage Certificate – if married (also Nikah Nama both in Bangla and English, for Muslim marriage in<br>A4 size Photocopy)<br>a. Divorce certificate (“talak namah”) – if applicable<br>b. Death Certificate – if applicable<br>c. Birth Certificate of your children –if applicable</p><p><strong>1.06</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>For minors below the age of 18 (if applicable) – proving legal parenthood:<br>a. copy of either birth certificate / proof of adoption / custody decree in case parents are divorced or<br>- if applicable - death certificate of parent ( Swedish or English translation is required)<br>“Letter of consent” from legal guardian, including his / her passport copy – legalized by a notary public<br>(only required in cases the legal guardian is not present during the visa appointment).</p><p><strong>1.07</strong></p><p><strong>Travel Insurance</strong></p><p>Insurance must be valid for the whole Schengen area. The Insurance must cover the repatriation costs up to 30,000 Euros. The Insurance must fully cover the whole period of stay within the Schengen area.<br>*The conditions must be stated either on the insurance document or on a separate confirmation letter.</p><p><strong>1.08</strong></p><p><strong>Forwarding Letter</strong></p><p>NOC from the applicant\'s company authority on the company\'s letterhead stating the applicant\'s name, designation, passport number, purpose, and duration of the visa.<br>**The NOC letter is highly important for your Schengen visa application.(Pay slips should be included in it.)</p><p><strong>1.09</strong></p><p><strong>Flight and hotel reservation</strong></p><p>Valid round trip Air Ticket confirmation and Hotel confirmation for the whole duration of the stay, or other documents proving accommodation is required.</p><p><strong>1.10</strong></p><p><strong>Cover letter and Tour Plan</strong></p><p>In a cover letter applicants have to mention about the purpose of visit and in a tour plan, the Travel Itinerary and places.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>2. Business Person</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>A valid passport that is original and at least Three / six months validity is essential. Moreover, the passport must have at least two blank pages.<br>Note: All previous passports and Visa\'s are required (if any).</p><p><strong>2.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo Specification</strong></p><p>Passport sized photographs (3.5 cm x 4.5cm)<br>a. Should not be older than 6 months.<br>b. A frontal view of the face covering 70-80% (32-26mm) of the biometric photo.<br>c. A uniform and white background.<br>d. Clear facial features<br>e. Head coverings are only accepted for religious reasons.<br>Do not glue or staple the pictures to the application form.</p><p><strong>2.03</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors/Applicants Financial Documents</strong></p><p>*Personal Bank Statement of last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency certificate.<br>*Company Bank Statement of last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency certificate (if business holder)<br>*TIN certificate<br>*Income Tax certificate (Last 2 years), Tax Return (ITR)<br>*Income Tax Certificate of the Company (Last 2 Years) (in case the applicant is a business holder).</p><p><strong>2.04</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants/Sponsors Proof of Occupation and Identity</strong></p><p>*Company memorandum.<br>*Visiting card.<br>*Updated Trade License<br>*Valid Passport copy, NID, Photo, Birth certificate.<br>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2.05</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of civil status</strong></p><p>Marriage Certificate – if married (also Nikah Nama both in Bangla and English, for Muslim marriage in<br>A4 size Photocopy)<br>a. Divorce certificate (“talak namah”) – if applicable<br>b. Death Certificate – if applicable<br>c. Birth Certificate of your children –if applicable</p><p><strong>2.06</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>For minors below the age of 18 (if applicable) – proving legal parenthood:<br>a. copy of either birth certificate / proof of adoption / custody decree in case parents are divorced or<br>- if applicable - death certificate of parent ( Swedish or English translation is required)<br>“Letter of consent” from legal guardian, including his / her passport copy – legalized by a notary public<br>(only required in cases the legal guardian is not present during the visa appointment).</p><p><strong>2.07</strong></p><p><strong>Travel Insurance</strong></p><p>Insurance must be valid for the whole Schengen area. The Insurance must cover the repatriation costs up to 30,000 Euros. The Insurance must fully cover the whole period of stay within the Schengen area.<br>*The conditions must be stated either on the insurance document or on a separate confirmation letter.<br>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2.08</strong></p><p><strong>Forwarding Letter</strong></p><p>The business pad states the applicant\'s name, designation, passport number, purpose, and duration of the visa.</p><p><strong>2.09</strong></p><p><strong>Flight and hotel reservation</strong></p><p>Valid round trip Air Ticket confirmation and Hotel confirmation for the whole duration of the stay, or other documents proving accommodation is required.</p><p><strong>2.10</strong></p><p><strong>Cover letter and Tour Plan</strong></p><p>In a cover letter applicants have to mention about the purpose of visit and in a tour plan, the Travel Itinerary and places.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>3. Professionals(Doctor, Engineer, CA etc)</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>3.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>A valid passport that is original and at least Three / six months validity is essential. Moreover, the passport must have at least two blank pages.<br>Note: All previous passports and Visa\'s are required (if any).</p><p><strong>3.02</strong></p><p><strong>Photo Specification</strong></p><p>Passport sized photographs (3.5 cm x 4.5cm)<br>a. Should not be older than 6 months.<br>b. A frontal view of the face covering 70-80% (32-26mm) of the biometric photo.<br>c. A uniform and white background.<br>d. Clear facial features<br>e. Head coverings are only accepted for religious reasons.<br>Do not glue or staple the pictures to the application form.</p><p><strong>3.03</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants/Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>*Personal Bank Statement of the last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency certificate.<br>*TIN certificate<br>*Income Tax certificate (Last 2 years), Tax Return (ITR)</p><p><strong>3.04</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants/Sponsors Proof of Occupation and Identity</strong></p><p>*Visiting Card<br>*If the applicant is a doctor, then he will show a BMDC certificate; If he is a lawyer, then he will have to show a Bar Council certificate; and others have to prove their occupation from their respective autonomous bodies.<br>*Valid Passport, NID, photo, and birth certificate.</p><p><strong>3.05</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of civil status</strong></p><p>Marriage Certificate – if married (also Nikah Nama both in Bangla and English, for Muslim marriage in<br>A4 size Photocopy)<br>a. Divorce certificate (“talak namah”) – if applicable<br>b. Death Certificate – if applicable<br>c. Birth Certificate of your children –if applicable</p><p><strong>3.06</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>For minors below the age of 18 (if applicable) – proving legal parenthood:<br>a. copy of either birth certificate / proof of adoption / custody decree in case parents are divorced or<br>- if applicable - death certificate of parent ( Swedish or English translation is required)<br>“Letter of consent” from legal guardian, including his / her passport copy – legalized by a notary public<br>(only required in cases the legal guardian is not present during the visa appointment).</p><p><strong>3.07</strong></p><p><strong>Travel Insurance</strong></p><p>Insurance