trong>4.03</strong></p><p><strong>Applications/Sponsors Proof of Occupation and Identity</strong></p><p>*Valid Passport, NID, photo, and birth certificate.<br>*Visa request letter from the educational institute or student card/evidence of school enrollment (if student)</p><p><strong>4.04</strong></p><p><strong>Applicants/Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>*Personal Bank Statement of the last 6 months &amp; Bank Solvency certificate.<br>*TIN certificate<br>*Income Tax Certificate (Last 2 years), Tax Return (ITR)</p><p><strong>4.05</strong></p><p><strong>Proof of civil status</strong></p><p>Marriage Certificate – if married (also Nikah Nama both in Bangla and English, for Muslim marriage in<br>A4 size Photocopy)<br>a. Divorce certificate (“talak namah”) – if applicable<br>b. Death Certificate – if applicable<br>c. Birth Certificate of your children –if applicable</p><p><strong>4.06</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Documents</strong></p><p>For minors below the age of 18 (if applicable) – proving legal parenthood:<br>a. copy of either birth certificate / proof of adoption / custody decree in case parents are divorced or<br>- if applicable - death certificate of parent ( Swedish or English translation is required)<br>“Letter of consent” from legal guardian, including his / her passport copy – legalized by a notary public<br>(only required in cases the legal guardian is not present during the visa appointment)</p><p><strong>4.07</strong></p><p><strong>Travel Insurance</strong></p><p>Insurance must be valid for the whole Schengen area. The Insurance must cover the repatriation costs up to 30,000 Euros. The Insurance must fully cover the whole period of stay within the Schengen area.<br>*The conditions must be stated either on the insurance document or on a separate confirmation letter.</p><p><strong>4.08</strong></p><p><strong>Flight and hotel reservation</strong></p><p>Valid Flight and Hotel bookings or the inviter\'s residence address is required<br>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>4.09</strong></p><p><strong>Cover letter and Tour Plan</strong></p><p>In a cover letter applicants have to mention about the purpose of visit and in a tour plan, the Travel Itinerary and places.</p><p><strong>4.10</strong></p><p><strong>Invitation Letter (If Any)</strong></p><p>An original copy of Invitation letter from company/ Organization or Friends and Family with evidence.</p><p><strong>4.11</strong></p><p><strong>Forwarding Letter</strong></p><p>The applicant\'s name, designation, passport number, purpose, and duration of the visa.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'facility_images/K39Ci9hQ00A4Y8FDtW59Vtuofb7kbBYGiaUwrwey.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-05-04 05:33:50', '2025-05-04 05:33:50', NULL),
(656, 350, NULL, 'Important Notes', '<p><br>Please contact the Visa department for Document processing after the payment. Visa rate may change without any prior notice</p>', 'facility_images/A5jQECwBEufjimOjEbC3gFKNFLXh6igMrE1QRsUv.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-05-04 05:34:08', '2025-05-04 05:34:08', NULL),
(657, 352, NULL, 'Required Documents for Visa', '<p><strong>Eligibility to Apply for Visa</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Any Bangladeshi Nationals are Eligible to Visit Maldives for purpose of tourism (having a valid MRP / E-Passport with at least 6 months validity) subject to provide some required Documents.<br>Also Applicant should,<br>• be a genuine visitor<br>• have enough funds to support his/her stay and leave</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Documents Requirements</strong></p><h2><strong>1. Service Holder</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>1.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a. Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>b) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>c) Attach all your old passports (if any).</p><p><strong>1.02</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>Sufficient Funds to be Endorsed in Passport (Cash / Card) to last for the intended period of stay in Maldives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>2. Business Person</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a. Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>b) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>c) Attach all your old passports (if any).</p><p><strong>2.02</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>Sufficient Funds to be Endorsed in Passport (Cash / Card) to last for the intended period of stay in Maldives.</p><h2>&nbsp;</h2><h2><strong>3. Professionals(Doctor, Engineer, CA etc)</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>3.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a. Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>b) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>c) Attach all your old passports (if any).</p><p><strong>3.02</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>Sufficient Funds to be Endorsed in Passport (Cash / Card) to last for the intended period of stay in Maldives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>4. Others</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>4.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>a. Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br>b) Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br>c) Attach all your old passports (if any).</p><p><strong>4.02</strong></p><p><strong>Sponsors Financial Documents</strong></p><p>Sufficient Funds to be Endorsed in Passport (Cash / Card) to last for the intended period of stay in Maldives.</p>', 'facility_images/qA0b8wvlcuVUbZUhZLhGer5ZJG7BSDhquhWO6eGX.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-05-04 06:18:31', '2025-05-04 06:18:31', NULL),
