(689, 368, NULL, 'Required Documents for Visa', '<p><strong>Eligibility to Apply for Visa</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Any Bangladeshi Nationals are Eligible to Apply for Tajikistan E-Visa (having a valid MRP / E-Passport with at least 6 months validity) subject to provide some required Documents.<br>Also Applicant should,<br>• be a genuine visitor<br>• have enough funds to support his/her stay and leave</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Documents Requirements</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>1. Service Holder</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>1.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>Machine Scanned copy of Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>2. Business Person</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>Machine Scanned copy of Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>3. Professionals(Doctor, Engineer, CA etc)</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>3.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>Machine Scanned copy of Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>4. Others</strong></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>4.01</strong></p><p><strong>Passport</strong></p><p>Machine Scanned copy of Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>e-Visa</strong></p><p><strong>The applicant must submit the necessary authentic and valid documents for a Tajikistan eVisa online. Once approved by the Embassy of Tajikistan, an electronic copy (softcopy) of the visa will be sent to the applicant for collection.</strong></p><p><strong>Tourist Visa</strong></p><p><strong>At the moment, a tourist visa is available in form of eVisa, which is valid for 90 days(single entry) and length of stay 60 days. Visitors under tourist visa are not allowed to accept any unauthorized employment, or attend school, or represent the foreign information media during their stay in Tajikistan.</strong></p>', 'facility_images/CZszCnrjyqIfQK7ZGCpVhiU7WWXFoc8pdsYqo77m.jpg', 1, NULL, '2025-05-06 05:59:33', '2025-05-06 05:59:55', NULL),
