(806, 383, 6, NULL, '<h2><strong>Silver Wave - A Luxury Water Villa</strong></h2><p>hings to keep in mind</p><p>An adequate amount of tea will be served on the boat. Travelers can have tea anytime they want.<br>There is a water filter on the boat. Travelers can drink water from that water filter.<br>The times mentioned in the itinerary are subject to change due to weather conditions, tides in the river, convenience of the travelers, and other unavoidable circumstances. Travelers are requested to cooperate with the operator/host/organizer in case of such circumstances.<br>The travelers are requested to contact with the tour operator/host/organizer incase they face any kind of trouble/problem during the tour.<br>Always be respectful of the rules and guidelines of the tourist spots.<br>Do not litter, use a disposable bag as a portable trash bin.<br>Travelers are strongly encouraged not to misbehave with any local inhabitants. Travelers are asked to seek help from the tour operator/host/organizer in case they need to contact any local people.<br>There is no separate dining space on this boat. Everyone will have their meals on the open deck of the boat.<br>Consumption of any sort of drugs is strictly prohibited.<br>In the case of a group tour, there will be other people who will travel with you.<br>If anyone wants to travel to Lakmachora on a bike then the traveler will have to bear&nbsp;the&nbsp;bike&nbsp;fare.</p>', NULL, 1, NULL, '2025-05-17 08:23:56', '2025-06-01 05:59:40', '16'),
(807, 383, 7, NULL, '<h2><strong>Travel tips</strong></h2><p>Traveling in Tanguar Haor and staying in houseboats can be a unique and rewarding experience. Here are some tips to ensure you have a memorable and enjoyable time:</p><p>During Your Stay:</p><p>Houseboat Comfort: While houseboats offer a unique experience, remember that their facilities might be basic. Expect simple amenities and embrace the rustic charm.<br>Respect Nature: Tanguar Haor is a delicate ecosystem. Be respectful of the environment; do not throw waste into the water or disturb wildlife.<br>Boat Safety: Houseboats should have safety equipment, including life jackets. Familiarize yourself with their location and wear them when necessary, especially during boat rides.<br>Cultural Respect: If interacting with local communities, be polite, ask for permission before taking photographs, and respect their way of life.<br>Meal Arrangements: Houseboats often provide meals as part of the package. Enjoy the local cuisine, but communicate any dietary preferences or restrictions in advance.<br>Electricity and Connectivity: Be prepared for limited or intermittent electricity and mobile network coverage. Carry portable chargers for your devices.<br>Exploring Tanguar Haor:</p><p>Birdwatching: Tanguar Haor is a haven for birdwatchers. Bring binoculars and a bird guidebook to identify the diverse avian species.<br>Boating: Enjoy the serene boat rides on the haor\'s tranquil waters. Sunrise and sunset boat trips offer captivating views. Silent boat rides are available near Tanguar Haor watch tower.<br>Fishing: If fishing is allowed, experience traditional fishing techniques with local fishermen.<br>Photography: Capture the breathtaking landscapes, vibrant sunsets, and unique moments during your stay.<br>Travelers are suggested to carry the following items:</p><p>Personal clothing<br>Towel/Gamcha<br>Sunglass<br>Hat<br>Personal Medicine<br>Personal Hygiene Products<br>Camera with extra battery<br>A copy of NID Card<br>Dry Food<br>Mosquito repellent lotion/cream<br>Sunscreen<br>Flashlight/Torch Light<br>Power Bank and charger<br>Swimwear<br>Rain gear (raincoat or poncho, umbrella)<br>Comfortable footwear (closed-toe shoes, sandals)<br>Personal medications<br>Trash bags (for responsible disposal)<br>Hand sanitizer<br>Moisturizer/lip balm<br>Small backpack or daypack<br>Copy of NID/Passport/Personal identification card.</p>', NULL, 1, NULL, '2025-05-17 08:24:22', '2025-05-17 08:24:22', '17'),
