(848, 387, 5, NULL, '<h2><strong>Description</strong></h2><p>Located in north-eastern Bangladesh, Tanguar haor is a river basin and a unique wetland ecosystem of national importance. The tour is ideal for you if you want to experience both adventures and serenity. You’ll have a traditional wooden boat with the necessary amenities as your home during the tour. During the tour, you’ll have mouth-watering delicacies more than three times a day while watching the beauty of the wetland from your private boat. The tour will also let you explore the picturesque beauty of Shimul Bagan, bathe in the mirror-like clear water, visit the popular lakes, and enjoy the view of the hills around. Hence, the tour will give you both tranquility to your soul and stories to tell.</p><p><strong>Places that will be covered in this tour are</strong></p><ul><li>Various Haors</li><li>Tangua</li><li>Watch Tower</li><li>Niladri Lake</li><li>Barikka Tila</li><li>Shimul Bagan</li><li>Jadukata River</li></ul><p><strong>child policy</strong><br><strong>Less than 5 years 30% \r\n\r\n5 to 10 years 50%\r\n\r\nMore than 10 years 100%</strong><br><strong>Food Menu</strong></p><p>Day 1</p><ul><li>Breakfast: Khichuri, egg, pickle, salad</li><li>Snacks: Tea, biscuits, lemon juice, fruits</li><li>Lunch: Rice, potato/vegetables, fried fish, dal, salad</li><li>Snacks: Semai, Tea Biscuits</li><li>Dinner: Rice, roast duck, bharta, dal, salad</li></ul><p>Day 2</p><ul><li>Breakfast: Khichuri/ paratha, vegetables, pickles, omelette, salad</li><li>Snacks- Tea, biscuits</li><li>Lunch: Rice, country chicken, bharta, dal, salad</li><li>Snacks: Tea Biscuits, Noodles</li></ul>', NULL, 1, NULL, '2025-05-18 04:30:34', '2025-05-28 06:48:52', '12'),
