(1040, 418, 5, NULL, '<p><br>Trip Food Menu (Tanguar Haor)</p><p>• • Meals • • Welcome Drinks Fresh Juice / Drinks&nbsp;<br>Items&nbsp;<br>•• Breakfast Bhuna Khichuri I Akhni, Chicken, Egg, Fried • Eggplant / Aloo Dum, Bread, Jelly, Cake, Pickle, Green Salad, Tea / Coffee, Mineral Water Morning Snacks Seasonal Fruits / Biscuits / Cake, Tea / Coffee&nbsp;<br>Lunch&nbsp;<br>Plain Rice, Mashed Items (2-3 types), Bottle Gourd with Shrimp, Spicy Fish Curry, Deshi Chicken / Quail Roast, Thick Lentil Soup, Fresh Salad,&nbsp;<br>Mineral Water, Dessert: Fimi / Payesh / Semai Evening Snacks Noodles, Spicy Puffed Rice Mix (Muri Makha), Vegetable Pakora / Chicken Pakora Dinner Plain Rice / Polao, Mashed Items (2 types), Mixed Vegetables / Small Fish, Fried Big Fish, Spicy Duck Curry, Thick Lentil Soup, Fresh Salad, Mineral Water, Dessert: Local Sweets / Yogurt&nbsp;<br><br>Shahid Siraj Lake (Niladri Lake) nestled within hills. this turquoise-blue lake. also known as Niladri Lake. is a hidden gem. Its crystal-clear waters, serene surroundings, and myth-like charm create an enchanting spot for nature enthusiasts.&nbsp;<br>Lakmachhara a pristine waterfall tucked amidst the hills. Lakmachhara captivates visitors with its cascading waters and untouched natural beauty. The soothing sound of water and the lush greenery around make it a perfect retreat for adventure seekers.&nbsp;<br>Jadukata River with its crystal-clear waters flowing down from the Meghalaya hills, is a captivating sight. Its famed for its pristine beauty. gentle rapids. and the majestic view of the mountains on the horizon.&nbsp;<br>Barikkatila Barikkatila is a stunning hilltop offering sweeping views of the surrounding haor and hills. Its unique rock formations and the panoramic scenery make it a popular spot for hiking and photography Shimul Bagan or Silk Cotton Garden. bursts into a fiery bloom during spring when thousands of red shimul flowers cover the landscape. A visit during this time is a visual treat, offering vibrant colors and a magical atmosphere</p><p>2 Days 1 Night Trip - Explore With Us&nbsp;<br>Surma River Flowing gracefully through the heart of Sylhet. the Surma River is a serene waterway known for its gentle currents. lush green banks, and charming boat rides. It offers a glimpse into the daily life of riverside communities and is perfect for a tranquil escape. Karcha/Shoni Haor A breathtaking wetland that transforms into a shimmering sea during the monsoon, Karcha/Shoni Haor is a paradise for birdwatchers and nature lovers alike. Its vast expanse of water reflects the sky, creating a mesmerizing landscape that feels endless. Tanguar Haor One of the largest wetlands in Bangladesh. Tanguar Haor is a sanctuary for migratory birds and aquatic Life. A UNESCO-recognized Ramsar site. it offers a magical experience of boating across its crystal-clear waters, surrounded by floating villages and the distant hills. Watch Tower offers a panoramic view of the surrounding haor landscapes. stretching far and wide across the shimmering waters and green fields. A perfect spot for capturing the golden hues of sunrise and sunset.&nbsp;<br>Tekerghat located near the Bangladesh-India border, is known for its unique limestone deposits and picturesque lake surrounded by hills.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, NULL, '2025-06-11 04:49:59', '2025-06-11 04:49:59', '19'),
